X9LBeIpT2RY.title: Carriage Owner Accused of Forging Collapsed Horse’s Age
X9LBeIpT2RY.description: The carriage driver whose horse collapses on the streets of New York City is being accused of lying about the animal's age. Colm McKeever is facing accusations that he tried to pass off the horse, Ryder, as 13 years old. Officials say the horse is actually 26 years old. Based on a standard identification chart, Ryder's tattoo indicates he was born in 1996. A horse rescuer says even if a horse does not have a tattooed number, an expert can estimate its age by examining its teeth.

Mz78oD1Up3E.title: Alec Baldwin May Potentially Face Criminal Charges in ‘Rust’ Shooting
Mz78oD1Up3E.description: According to new reports, Alec Baldwin could be criminally charged in connection with his role in the fatal shooting of cinematographer Halyna Hutchins during the filming of “Rust.” New Mexico prosecutors say as many as four people, including Baldwin, could potentially be criminally charged. Baldwin has repeatedly claimed he was told the gun had blanks and he did not pull the trigger when Hutchins was accidentally fatally shot.

However, the show is bringing memories of Dahmer's vile deeds flooding back to his survivors. Preston Davis, who was sexually assaulted by him, says he felt more empathy for the victims' families. Billy Joe Capshaw, who was also sexually assaulted by Dahmer in the Army, says the show is bringing back horrible memories.

3jzpQnHgGu0.title: Florida Prepares for Powerful Hurricane Ian
3jzpQnHgGu0.description: The state of Florida is bracing for the impact of Hurricane Ian. Forecasters are modeling where the storm will make landfall and the consensus is that Tampa will take a major hit. Experts are predicting the storm will be the worst hurricane to hit Tampa in over 100 years with 15-feet waves and winds up to 135 miles per hour. A storm surge could send up to eight feet of water into Tampa, overwhelming the city's flood defenses.

oMS3RnSPUEo.title: Could a Massive Quake Hit Palos Verdes, California?
oMS3RnSPUEo.description: For Californians, the possibility of an earthquake is always a concern. But a new study has Palos Verdes residents on alert. Researchers are looking at a fault system, made of multiple strands, going through the region. A study from Harvard University shows this segmented network of faults could be interconnected. Which means they could produce a massive tremor with a possible 7.8 magnitude. Inside Edition Digital has more.

g0UXIW3dBt4.title: Rescuers Die as Typhoon Smashes Island
g0UXIW3dBt4.description: The most powerful typhoon to hit the Philippines this year slammed into the coast in Burdeos town in Quezon province before nightfall on Sunday. It weakened as it barreled overnight across the main Luzon region, where officials say thousands of people were moved to emergency shelters. Gov. Daniel Fernando of Bulacan province said five rescuers who were using a boat to help residents trapped in floodwaters were hit by a collapsed wall and drowned in the raging waters.

prmSYocwoKM.title: Sheriff Uses CPR to Save Baby
prmSYocwoKM.description: A Lee County, Florida, sheriff is a hero after saving a baby using CPR. Deputy Weaver, a school resource officer, was working at the time. The mother was in the parent pick-up line and noticed that her baby in the backseat wasn’t breathing. She exited her car and frantically called for help, and Deputy Weaver ran over to assist. He calmly took the baby and started back thrusts and chest compressions. This ultimately saved the baby’s life. Inside Edition Digital has more.

je9jEBOcZ60.title: Man Reunites With His Biological Mom After 20 Years
je9jEBOcZ60.description: A Utah woman reunited with her biological son 20 years after putting him up for adoption. Holly Shearer was just 15 years old when she found out she was pregnant. Shearer made the difficult decision to put her baby up for adoption. She selected Angela Hulleberg, who was unable to have her own biological children, to adopt baby Benjamin. When he turned 20, Benjamin received a message from Shearer on social media. After meeting for dinner, they discovered they worked at the same hospital.

I_It7YaYzAQ.title: Amazon Driver Saves Family During Delivery Route

Kevin says it took the family a minute to realize their house was on fire. The 22-year-old helped get the entire family out, even the pets. ukVjXFIOdvs.description: In New York City, electric unicycles are everywhere. Known as ECUs, some are capable of reaching 60 miles per hour. He also believes electric unicycles are the future for commuting through busy streets.

yRLRQ6-4rAE.title: Iran President Cancels CNN Interview Over Headscarf Demand

TxwZFimGp60.title: School Shooter Seeks Parole After 25 Years in Prison
TxwZFimGp60.description: Michael Carneal is seeking parole after being sentenced to life 25 years ago for the Heath High School shooting. She is one of five students wounded in the shooting. During his hearing, Carneal told the parole board that voices in his head told him to kill.

Hightower says the thieves hit her at least three times, pistol-whipped her then stole her 11-month-old French bulldog, Milani. xg_RlZ7I0u4.description: Protesters marched and spoke in Australia this week, during an official day of mourning for the late Elizabeth II. The protesters want to do away with the monarchy, as one marcher told Reuters, "The monarchy represents everything that's wrong with the world today.” Australia is one of the Commonwealth nations, and technically is a constitutional monarchy. Charles III is the king of Australia. The queen’s death has occasioned a reassessment of the role of the monarchy.

RJu1UALUQf0.title: Route 91 Harvest Festival Mass Shooting Survivor on Life Now
RJu1UALUQf0.description: Five years ago, thousands were having the time of their lives at the Route 91 Harvest Festival, a country music event on The Strip in Las Vegas, when suddenly bullets began hailing from the sky. Stephen Paddock had opened fire on the crowd of 22,000 from the Mandalay Bay hotel, killing 60 and injuring hundreds. Autumn Bignami and her husband were there on Oct. 1, 2017. Autumn was shot three times and fought to survive. She is sharing her story with Inside Edition Digital’s Andrea Swindall.

FRJa6Hu5Qz8.title: Eva LaRue Shares Her Experience Being Stalked
FRJa6Hu5Qz8.description: "CSI: Miami" actress Eva LaRue is opening up about the nightmare she has been living off-screen. For 12 years, a stalker terrorized the actress, sending her and her young daughter threatening letters. They were all signed the same way — "Love, Freddy Krueger" — based on the fictional monster from “A Nightmare on Elm Street.” FBI agents were able to extract DNA from letters the suspect wrote. James David Rogers was later charged with stalking and mailing threatening communications.

cpd87xxb2BU.title: Passenger Punches Flight Attendant Mid-Flight
cpd87xxb2BU.description: A passenger sucker punched a flight attendant during a flight from Mexico to California. The plane was headed from the resort town of Cabo San Lucas to Los Angeles when the violence erupted 20 minutes into the fight. The man reportedly became enraged when he was not allowed to use the bathroom in first class. He suddenly lunged at the flight attendant, throwing a shocking punch. After the sucker punch, at least three passengers jumped in to subdue the unruly man.

e-nE-w72Yrg.title: Why Are Some Electronic Bikes and Scooters Catching Fire?
e-nE-w72Yrg.description: Several electric scooters and electric bikes are bursting into flames. According to New York City Fire Department, e-battery-related fires are up a whopping 233% in two years in the Big Apple. The fires have resulted in 163 injuries and 10 deaths, including a 5-year-old girl who was killed in an apartment building fire. California couple Daniel and Linda Jones say they lost everything when their electric scooter caught on fire. Electrical engineer Brad Davis says many fires are caused by overcharging or faulty batteries.

EukytXJZkdY.title: Ebola Outbreak Declared
EukytXJZkdY.description: According to the World Health Organization, an Ebola outbreak has been declared in Uganda. Health officials have found a dozen cases of the viral infection, also known as Ebola hemorrhagic fever. Ebola is spread through contact with bodily fluids. It can take several days for symptoms to appear. The disease causes both internal and external bleeding, and is often fatal. Authorities in Uganda are working to trace the source of the infection, and isolate those who may have been infected.

1fwNLkG787Q.title: 18-Year-Old Gets Elected to Idaho School Board
1fwNLkG787Q.description: Shiva Rajbhandari, an 18-year-old senior, just made history in Idaho. He’s the first student to ever serve on the Boise School District Board of Trustees. And he beat out a candidate endorsed by a local far-right group. “He was endorsed by this far-right group. He was repeatedly asked to disavow this endorsement and he refused to,” Shiva said. He spoke to Inside Edition Digital about what he hopes to achieve while serving.

AMKdxmtyXqw.title: Single Mom of 3 Says Hoverboard Fire Destroyed Their Home
AMKdxmtyXqw.description: An Illinois family is lucky to be alive after they say a charging hoverboard broke out into flames late at night. Beth Hughes says it started in her 8-year-old daughter’s bedroom. She told KMOV she and her three kids were all jolted awake by the explosion and all made it out of the house without injury, but their home was completely destroyed. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

1T1aRkv9J9k.title: Baby Girl Pulled From Rubble of Building Collapse in Jordan
1T1aRkv9J9k.description: A baby pulled from the rubble of a collapsed building in Jordan was a symbol of hope for many. Reports say at least 25 people were in a building when it collapsed in Amman on September 13. Rescuers dug through the rubble for more than 80 hours looking for survivors. Days later when the search was called off, 10 people had been found injured and 14 had perished. Baby Malak was one of the lucky ones, according to the country’s Civil Defense. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

cb-XBfj5LoA.title: Are Some Restaurants Serving Fake Scallops?
cb-XBfj5LoA.description: Some restaurants have served their customers fake scallops. Inside Edition gathered samples of scallops from a popular fish market in New York City. They were sent to Applied Food Technologies in Florida, where Molly Sims and her colleagues specialize in seafood DNA analysis. The lab found there wasn't any scallop within the food. Instead, surimi, a fish paste, was found within the "scallops." A seafood expert says of all the creatures in the sea, scallops are the most frequently substituted.

It was the most-watched TV event of all time, dethroning the opening ceremony for the 1996 Atlanta Olympics. At No. 3 is the 2008 Beijing Olympics opening ceremony with three billion viewers. No. 4 is Princess Diana's funeral at two billion viewers. And at No. 5 is the late Freddie Mercury and his band Queen at 1985's Live Aid benefit concert.

dNs3AjApcTE.title: Woman Injured When Part of Construction Vehicle Lands on Car
dNs3AjApcTE.description: A woman narrowly escaped death when part of a construction vehicle landed on her car. Danielle Cruz tells WCBS in New York that it happened while she was driving to class at Lehman College. She was stopped at a red light when part of a boom truck from a nearby construction site came crashing down on top of her. The city’s Department of Buildings says a preliminary investigation found the boom truck was lifting rebar to the roof of the building. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

M1O3hHUjwPU.description: An elephant needed some help after it got stuck in a pond. Reports say it happened in China’s Yunnan Province. Concerned witnesses called wildlife officials for help after four elephants fell into the water, but when the officials arrived just one elephant was left, and was struggling to get out. A rescuer had an idea to break part of the wall and let some of the water out. It seemed to be just what the animal needed to save itself. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

OnfWghWW0Qc.description: Researchers with the National Autonomous University of Mexico say they have no scientific explanation for it, and that it is just a coincidence. However, it is quite a stunning one. On the exact same day, September 19, over the course of 37 years, major earthquakes have rocked Mexico. The latest was on Monday, where officials saId one person died in the natural disaster. Inside Edition Digital’s Stepanie Officer explains.

EVo8Ba7FaLI.title: Who Adopted the Beagles Rescued From Breeding Facility?
EVo8Ba7FaLI.description: All 4,000 beagles rescued from a lab and breeding facility in Virginia were adopted. When the facility shut down last July, all the pups were sent to animal shelters across the nation by the Humane Society of the United States. Now, all of those beagles finally have homes. Meghan Markle and Prince Harry adopted one of the beagles, who's a happy camper at their California estate. New Jersey Governor Phil Murphy and his wife, Tammy, also adopted one of the beagles named Morty.

XMWLaiKkyzg.title: London Begins to Clean Up After Queen Elizabeth’s Funeral
XMWLaiKkyzg.description: London is returning to normal a day after Queen Elizabeth II’s funeral. It's hard to believe that thousands of mourners arrived to pay their respects to the queen. With crowds completely dispersed, the clean-up at Buckingham Palace has begun. Former President Donald Trump is also mocking the seating arrangements in Westminster Abbey that put President Biden and first lady Jill Biden 14 rows back at the funeral. He says "If I were President, they wouldn’t have sat me back there."

03Z_-VJowPM.title: LSU Student Shot Dead in Car at Railroad Crossing
03Z_-VJowPM.description: The heartbroken father of a slain college senior is pleading for help to track down the murderer. Twenty-one-year-old Allie Rice was shot multiple times through the windshield of her car when it stopped at a railroad crossing in Baton Rouge. The marketing major from Louisiana State University had been on a night out with friends. Her father, Paul Rice, says she was in the wrong place at the wrong time. No motive or suspects have been named.

vPgaPiIl0UI.title: Tips for Finding Anti-Aging Beauty Products
vPgaPiIl0UI.description: Inside Edition teamed up with RoC® Skincare and its partner, dermatologist Dr. Sheila Farhang, to provide tips for people seeking a youthful look. She suggests searching for beauty products with ingredients like retinol and hyaluronic acid. Retinol works to increase cell renewal and stimulate collagen production. Hyaluronic acid pulls in moisture and plumps up skin to decrease the appearance of fine lines. Dr. Farhang recommends RoC’s Retinol Correxion Max Hydration Cream, which contains those two ingredients.

Sherri Papini's sister is also denouncing her. Sheila Koester says her sister feels no remorse or guilt for the untold damage she has caused.

In Yuli, a landslide trapped nearly 400 tourists on a mountain famous for orange daylilies. Inside Edition Digital’s Stephanie Officer has the details.

Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

EFg99Nj7rnU.title: ‘Rat to Cash’ Program Pays Bounty for Bags of Rodents
EFg99Nj7rnU.description: A city in the Philippines has instituted a ‘Rat to Cash’ program, offering money in exchange for rodents. Rat to Cash hopes to curb the spread of disease during the rainy season in Marikina City, a suburb of Manila. Rats can carry a bacteria known as Leptospirosis. It causes a water-borne disease that can be spread through rat urine. According to the CDC, symptoms of Leptospirosis include fever, headache, and intestinal problems. It can lead to liver and kidney failure, as well as meningitis.

The armored tractor-trailer was transporting the jewels to a gem show in Pasadena, California, before the heist. The driver, who was eating dinner, says he returned 27 minutes later to find the truck had been broken into. The guard who was sleeping claimed, "He did not see or hear anything unusual."

tydoxGdrSyQ.title: Toddler Accidentally Killed When Overturned Cement Truck Crushes Car
tydoxGdrSyQ.description: A toddler was accidentally killed when a cement truck fell off of a Texas highway overpass and landed on the SUV. Inside the smashed vehicle were 2-year-old twins strapped into their car seats, along with their mom and grandma. The little girl, Melanie Resendiz, survived, but her brother Nicolas Resendiz was crushed to death. The horrific crash happened three weeks ago in Houston. Police have not filed charges and say the driver is distraught and cooperating with the investigation.

q3uuIz3azqk.title: Ultramarathon Runner Attacked by Coyote
q3uuIz3azqk.description: An ultra-marathoner was attacked by a coyote while out on a 150-mile trail run. The incident happened on a popular trail in Marin county, California. Dean Karnazes heard some footsteps coming behind him. When he swung around, a coyote attacked him from behind. Karnazes was able to fight off the coyote using his ultra-marathon poles. Experts say attacks by coyotes are becoming more common due to the animal losing their fear of humans.

H496qKcwmHY.title: Anne Heche Dead at 53
H496qKcwmHY.description: Actress Anne Heche died at the age of 53. Her death comes days after she crashed her car into a home in California, causing it to erupt into flames. Heche's representative says she suffered from an anoxic brain injury when she was trapped in the burning car due to a lack of oxygen. OdoztGy8X8s.title: Case of Slain School Teacher Gets Reopened 10 Years Later
OdoztGy8X8s.description: The case of a beloved schoolteacher found dead with 20 stab wounds is now being reopened after more than a decade. In 2011, Ellen Greenberg was found dead by her fiancé at their apartment in Philadelphia. She had ten stab wounds on the back of her neck, eight on her chest, one on her abdomen and another one on her scalp. Greenberg's death was at first ruled a homicide but was later changed to suicide. Her parents have spent the last 11 years fighting that ruling.

He was driving home with his 2-year-old daughter. Cops say he stopped his vehicle to move a tire obstructing the road. That's when he was gunned down. Police believe the tire was left in the middle of the street to lure him out of his car. Bridegan's widow, Kirsten, says their daughter is struggling with what she saw that night.

hoHfM7rnitE.title: Betty White’s Personal Items Up for Auction
hoHfM7rnitE.description: Although the nation's heart broke last year when Betty White died just shy of her 100th birthday, her legacy will still live on. About 1,500 of her personal items are set to be sold at a Beverly Hills auction next month. The collection includes White's famous tracksuit she wore on "Hot in Cleveland" and the turquoise gown she wore when she accepted her 2010 lifetime achievement award at the SAG-AFTRA awards. Also, White's items from "The Golden Girls" will been the block.

Linda Krockenberger co-founded the Arabian Desert Camel Riding Centre in order to share her love of the animals. “There are other places to ride, but usually they don't offer such an in-depth experience with the animal, or that people can come repeatedly, and they can build relationships with the animals,” Krockenberger told Reuters. Inside Edition Digital’s Stephanie Officer explains.

StVT4PMqlPg.description: Humans aren’t the only ones who need to beat the heat, so a fashion company and a veterinarian teamed up to help our furry family members during a heatwave. Maternity clothing line Sweet Mommy created tiny mesh outfits that help circulate cool air around an animal’s body with the help of a little fan. Even the tiniest canine can take a walk wearing one of these outfits. The fan and battery pack are so small, they only weigh about 3 ounces.

aCU3p8k25uM.description: A former teacher in Texas has pleaded guilty to sexually abusing a 13-year-old student. For three years, Marka Bodine sent him explicit photos, videos and texts. According to police, Bodine, 32, and the student had sex in her classroom and in her car. However, there's controversy over what some say is an incredibly light sentence. Bodine was sentenced to only 60 days, although prosecutors asked for a maximum 40-year prison term.

It's believed they were hiding from the storm under a tree when lightning struck. Massive lighting bolts were seen striking a tree in Lafayette Square. Two other people were rushed to the hospital with life-threatening injuries sustained in the weather.

Mv0_ZMunJbg.title: Lost Beluga Whale Swims Up Seine River
Mv0_ZMunJbg.description: Marine biologists and rescue teams are trying to beat the clock in order to save the life of a beluga whale. Experts say the sight of a beluga whale in France’s Seine River is not a good sign. The beluga whale has been tracked about 45 miles northwest of Paris, quite far from its native, frigid Arctic waters. Conservation groups say the whale needs food and a guide out of the Seine’s freshwater back to cold saltwater.

PoF69AuCafY.title: Liquor Store Owner Goes Back to Work After Thwarting Theft
PoF69AuCafY.description: The 80-year-old liquor store owner that opened fire on an armed robber with a shotgun is now back at work. He was greeted with a stream of grateful customers stopping by to say well done. When the robber came into the store with an assault rifle, Craig Cope quickly shot the person with a shotgun, hitting the suspect's arm. As the suspects raced off, the owner stood guard waiting for police to show up. Moments later, Cope suffered a heart attack which he has recovered from.

-FkZFY98pQ4.title: Tick-Borne Virus Leaves Toddler in Hospital for 2 Weeks
-FkZFY98pQ4.description: A Pennsylvania toddler is recovering from a life-threatening infection caused by a tick. Jamie Simoson found a tick on her 3-year-old son, Jonny. Two weeks later he got sick with a headache and high fever. The boy was diagnosed with Meningoencephalitis, caused by the Powassan Virus. Jonny spent almost two weeks in the hospital because of the tick-borne virus, and is now in speech, occupational, and physical therapy to recover from side effects of the disease.

91vIIwZscaU.description: Dramatic body camera video shows a woman being rescued from powerful flooding in Arizona. Apache Junction Police said on July 28 alone, the department “responded to 24 different calls for service related to flooding.” Sue Teder says she was in a car with her dog when a flash flood surprised her, pushing her vehicle backwards and spinning. Wile Teder made it out of the sinking car to safety, her 11-week-old puppy, Claire, has not been seen since that day.

w5cHLfXa3w0.title: Massive Dinosaur Fossil Sold at Auction for Over $6M
w5cHLfXa3w0.description: A Gorgosaurus dinosaur fossil sold for $6.1 million at a New York City auction house. The 9-foot-tall and 22-foot-long dinosaur is a relative of the Tyrannosaurus Rex. They both share similar characteristics like a gigantic head, dozens of sharp curved teeth, and two small arms. According to Sotheby’s, the skeleton was the first of its kind available for private ownership. It was sold to an anonymous buyer.

The suspect approached him and demanded property, according to cops. Police say the victim ran and the suspect followed and tried to shoot him, but his gun failed to fire. Afterward, the suspect drove away in a black sedan with tinted windows. The suspect is described as a Black man who is 18 to 25 years old. Inside Edition Digital has more.

dBNRdkWeFFA.title: 2 Dead, At Least 10 Injured After Boat Capsizes
dBNRdkWeFFA.description: At least two people are dead, including a child, and 10 others injured after a boat capsized in the Hudson River. Twelve people were on board when it capsized just before 3 p.m. on Monday afternoon. The captains of two passing ferries stopped to help save the passengers, who were tourists visiting from Colombia. “This is a tragic day for New Yorkers, indeed it may well have been worse,” NYPD Commissioner Keechant Sewel told reporters. Inside Edition Digital’s Stephanie Officer has the details.

kL37nylIhIg.title: Jackie Evancho Shares She Is Battling Anorexia
kL37nylIhIg.description: “America's Got Talent” finalist Jackie Evancho reveals she has anorexia, which led to her osteoporosis diagnosis. In the end, it took 102 hours, but Rahul is alive and has been reunited with his family.

OrjmZ6t-5vE.title: Ancient Egyptian Mummies Discovered
OrjmZ6t-5vE.description: Archaeologists in present-day Egypt recently discovered a trove of artifacts, dating back some 2,500 years ago. The find includes 250 sarcophagi – which contain mummified remains – and 150 bronze statues of ancient gods. There were also bronze containers used in rites for Isis, the goddess of fertility. The relics were found in the Saqqara necropolis, near the Egyptian capital of Cairo. Archaeological work has been going on there since 2018.

tfkjwavDJ_k.title: Rare Monkeypox Virus Found in Several Countries
tfkjwavDJ_k.description: Cases of monkeypox, a relatively rare virus, have been confirmed in Europe, Australia and North America. Some health officials say there is no reason to panic. The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention says initial symptoms of monkeypox include “fever, malaise, headache, weakness,” swollen lymph nodes and a distinctive rash. “Because monkeypox virus is closely related to the virus that causes smallpox, the smallpox vaccine can protect people from getting monkeypox,” according to the CDC.

qgkCVhPo_1A.description: When Kim Kardashian wore Marilyn Monroe’s famous ‘JFK birthday’ dress to the Met Gala, she was given a unique gift: what was purported to be a lock of Monroe’s hair. But Scott Fortner, a collector of Marilyn Monroe artifacts, says the hair is counterfeit. Ripley’s Believe It or Not, who gave Kardashian the hair, says it’s the real deal. John Corcoran, Director of Exhibits and Archives for Ripley’s, told Inside Edition, “This was purchased at a very reputable auction.”

rZe1q8_S7Aw.title: 130,000 Newer Teslas Recalled for Blank Screens
rZe1q8_S7Aw.description: Tesla is recalling 2021 and 2022 Model S and Model X, as well as the Model 3 and Model Y from 2022. The National Highway Traffic Safety Administration says the center touchscreens may overheat during the fast-charging process, causing the infotainment system to restart or appear blank. The government agency wrote in a May 3 safety report that this “may increase the risk of a collision.” According to the Associated Press, this is the 11th vehicle recall for Tesla since Jan. 27, 2022.

gs3iHcV3-T4.title: Why Do Some People Help Inmates to Escape?
gs3iHcV3-T4.description: It’s the question captivating America: Why would a trusted corrections officer risk it all to help a convicted murderer? Toby Young knows exactly how it could happen. Young ran a volunteer dog-training program at a state prison in Kansas, where she met and fell in love with a man named John Manard. He was serving a life sentence for murder. In 2006, Young helped sneak Manard out of prison in a dog crate, and they went on the run.

e5cO9nhJZuc.title: Is Elon Musk on Vladimir Putin’s Hit List?
e5cO9nhJZuc.description: Elon Musk is known for his attention-getting tweets. But recently he seemed to suggest that Russian president Vladimir Putin might wish him harm. Tech billionaire Musk has been threatened by a Putin crony for sending communications technology to Ukraine. “For this, Elon, you will be held accountable like an adult,” the head of Russia’s space agency is quoted as saying. That prompted Musk to tweet, “If I die under mysterious circumstances, it’s been nice knowin ya.”

xEKaaHmOaKk.title: Antarctica’s Emperor Penguins Could Be Extinct in 30 Years
xEKaaHmOaKk.description: Antarctica’s emperor penguins are in severe danger of becoming extinct, all thanks to climate change. The birds rely on ice to produce and live. But the region is dealing with warmer temperatures, rain and ice slides. Because of this, researchers think the penguins could disappear in 30 to 40 years. This happened a few years ago with the Halley colony in the Weddell Sea. Inside Edition Digital has more.

BWXMR0L-XJk.title: Outcry After 6-Year-Old Runs Full ‘Flying Pig’ Marathon
BWXMR0L-XJk.description: How young is too young to run a full, 26-mile marathon? That’s a question many are asking in the wake of news that 6-year-old Rainier Crawford took part in Cincinnati’s annual “Flying Pig” marathon with his parents and siblings. The little boy finished the race in 8 hours, 36 minutes. Rainier’s father, Ben Crawford, says the boy was not forced to run, but was allowed to because he “begged” to join the rest of his family.

RaiBI00zMaM.title: Duct-Taped Airline Passenger Sentenced to Prison
RaiBI00zMaM.description: Video of Maxwell Berry howling while duct-taped to an airline seat went viral in August of 2021. Police say he groped the breasts and backsides of two female flight attendants, and is seen on video punching a male attendant. Flight attendants used seat-belt extenders and tape to keep him seated. Berry pled guilty to three counts of assault and the judge gave him 60 days in prison with one year of supervised release.

rIm7dL5tsg0.title: New Jesus Statue Is Taller Than Rio’s ‘Christ the Redeemer’
rIm7dL5tsg0.description: Tourists flock to see Christ the Redeemer tower over Copacabana and Ipanema beaches in Brazil. Now Encantado, a small town in southern Brazil, wants some of those tourism dollars for itself. Encantado has built the 141-foot-tall Christ the Protector statue in order to attract some of Rio de Janeiro’s tourists. The new statue is 16 feet taller than Christ the Redeemer. The organization that began building the statue in 2019 says that makes Christ the Protector “the largest Christ in the world."

yKSvv4bszQ0.title: Mom Kills Pit Bull and Stabs Another That Attacked Her Child
yKSvv4bszQ0.description: A mother came to the rescue when her two pit bulls attacked her daughter, killing one of the animals and injuring the other. Jamie Morales says late one night when the two dogs were let into the house, they attacked her daughter, Ruby, 1. Several family members jumped on them to try to get them off. LD9wfkUVRMw.title: Hunt for Killer of 10-Year-Old Lily Peters Ramps Up
LD9wfkUVRMw.description: A 10-year-old Wisconsin girl who vanished Sunday night while riding home on her bike has been discovered dead in the woods just blocks from her house. Authorities warned parents to be vigilant and to drop off and pick up their kids from school. The heartbreaking discovery was made Monday morning by investigators who searched through the night for Iliana "Lily" Peters, a fourth grader in Chippewa Falls. The girl's body was found not far from her bike, near a walking path. The suspect is at large.

WS8RQZOHQtI.title: Orphaned Mountain Lion ‘Rose’ Becomes Social Media Darling
WS8RQZOHQtI.description: An orphaned mountain lion is being nursed back to health by the Oakland Zoo. Caregivers named her Rose, and believe she’s about 4 or 5 months old. An average cub of that age would be about 30 pounds. Rose only weighed 8 pound, 8 ounces. She is being bottle fed formula and spoon fed. Doctors are “guardedly optimistic” about Rose’s recovery. The Oakland Zoo is giving updates on baby Rose on its social media pages.

6aj0trK9eEA.title: Teen Entrepreneur Inspired by Autistic Brother
6aj0trK9eEA.description: A young entrepreneur is drawing inspiration from his brother to help others. Jose Rodriguez is just 18 years old, but his company is helping to improve the lives of people with autism, like his brother Joel. Since they were kids, Jose watched Joel struggle with stress-related fidgeting. He later saw how much fidget spinners and toys helped Joel calm down, but Joel would often lose them. So Jose created a shirt with an attached fidget toy — and won a full ride to business school in the process.

qrnyPoP1SfI.description: In the aftermath of Russia’s retreat from Kyiv, horrific scenes of dead bodies lining the streets of Ukrainian cities have emerged. Many are calling the apparent murders of civilians by Russian troops war crimes. Russia is claiming that the grim scenes were staged, but CBS News correspondent Debora Patta, who witnessed these horrors, said that it would be “impossible to stage” such gruesome scenes. Satellite images taken two weeks ago, before Russian troops withdrew, show bodies in the streets.

Satellite images taken two weeks ago, before Russian troops withdrew, show bodies in the streets.

HObghTAcxFY.title: I-65 Serial Killer Identified in Cold Case Investigation
HObghTAcxFY.description: A serial killer known as the I-65 Killer has finally been identified. Indiana State Police say Harry Edward Greenwell was the person who killed at least three women along interstate 65 in the late 1980s. Police used investigative genealogy to ID Greenwell, based on evidence left at the crime scenes. Sgt. Glen Fifield of the Indiana State Police announced at a press conference that “the match was 99.9999% positive.” Greenwell died in 2013.

YvD4JM-I2FQ.title: Highly Contagious Bird Flu Detected in 15 States
YvD4JM-I2FQ.description: A highly contagious strain of avian flu is spreading to several states in the U.S. Wisconsin is the latest state to report finding h5n1 – the scientific name for the avian flu – after discovering it in a commercial chicken flock. Avian flu has now been found in 15 states. Cross-species spread is possible, though not likely. Dr. William Schaffner of Vanderbilt University Medical Center told CBS News, “It's a very rare event, it requires very close association of the human with the bird.”

They're also making spike strips to slow down the invaders.

llbljvxTQJw.description: One year after Lady Gaga’s dog walker was nearly shot to death while fighting off vicious dognappers, the hero is living far away from Hollywood, in a camper in Austin, Texas. Ryan Fischer suffered a collapsed lung and nerve damage from the bullet that entered just below his neck and tore into his shoulder blade. He told Inside Edition that staying in Hollywood became a painful reminder of the trauma he suffered, so he decided to hit the road, taking inspiration from the film “Nomadland.”

5MebluWiMQI.title: World's Largest Cargo Plane Destroyed in Ukraine
5MebluWiMQI.description: Officials inside Ukraine are reporting the Antonov An-225 cargo plane has been destroyed in a Russian assault on an airfield near Kyiv. The Antonov An-225 was also called Mriya, which translates to “the dream” in Ukrainian. The Antonov An-225 Mriya was designed as part of the former Soviet Union's space program. Mriya was the only one completed. The Ukrainian Defense Industry estimates it will cost over $3 Billion to restore the plane. "The restoration shall be time consuming," they said.

He told authorities two gunmen tried to force him out of his car, but he fooled them by saying there was a police car behind them. That’s when he says the gunfire started. Authorities think the suspects were driving a red car and hope people who live in the area may have caught them on their doorbell cameras.

s215f2KFcqU.title: Drew Carey Discusses Pain Around Ex-Fiancée’s Murder
s215f2KFcqU.description: Drew Carey opens up about his late ex-fiancée Amie Harwick. Harwick, a well-known Hollywood sex therapist, was murdered two years after the couple had broken off their engagement. In February 2020, officers arrived on the scene to respond to a call of a woman screaming. Harwick’s roommate met them on the street, who told police that Harwick was being attacked by an ex-boyfriend. When police searched the residence, they found Harwick unresponsive, lying on the ground under a third-story balcony.

Y7AnDgYU_qs.title: How NASA Is Working to Prevent an Asteroid From Hitting Earth
Y7AnDgYU_qs.description: Could an asteroid hit Earth? Hollywood has explored the premise of planet-killer asteroids before in blockbusters like “Armageddon,” “Deep Impact,” and “Don’t Look Up.” But for NASA, it’s not science fiction. Last November, NASA launched the Double Asteroid Redirection Mission, or DART, which aims to test whether asteroids can be diverted from a collision course with Earth. The asteroid they’re testing it on is 7 million miles away, and is not a danger to our planet.

WgMQRBv_S-Q.title: Suspect Found Dead After Hospital Worker Set on Fire
WgMQRBv_S-Q.description: A worker at a hospital in New Jersey was set on fire by another employee. Prosecutors allege the suspect was Nicholas Pagano, a traveling nurse working as a contractor at Hackensack Medical Center in New Jersey. Police were searching for him and later found him dead from a self-inflicted gunshot wound. The victim is being treated for third degree burns at a different hospital.

yzKBRdm2u_4.title: Police Crossing Guard Who Saved Girl Honored by Governor
yzKBRdm2u_4.description: A real-life superhero jumped into action to save a little girl — but she wasn’t wearing a cape. Crossing guard Corporal Annette Goodyear, who is also a police officer, was on duty in North East, Maryland, when 11-year-old Violet Watt entered the crosswalk. She held her hand up to signal for the oncoming car to stop, but the vehicle wasn’t slowing down. Just as it was about to strike Violet, she pushed the girl out of the way and was hit. The governor is honoring her heroism.

tzaAuCJ1dqs.title: Joe Rogan Used N-Word in Now-Deleted Podcast Episodes
tzaAuCJ1dqs.description: Joe Rogan is facing backlash for repeatedly saying the n-word on his podcast, which came to light after a video clip compilation of over 20 instances of the host using the racist language went viral on social media. The n-word compilation video went viral after it was posted by singer India Arie to explain why she had joined other singers in removing her music from Spotify. Rogan, who has been in the hot seat over spreading COVID-19 misinformation on his podcast, removed 70 episodes from Spotify.

z7QkDMI3MHU.title: Meat Loaf Wished to Walk Daughter Down the Aisle Before Dying
z7QkDMI3MHU.description: To the world, he was Meat Loaf, but to her, he was just “Dad.” Amanda Aday is speaking out today about her father’s final days. UCvA5W7lsx4.title: Judge Gives Probation to Parents Who Accidentally Drowned Kids
UCvA5W7lsx4.description: Two parents ignored barriers and warning signs to go joyriding in a flooded creek and three children drowned as a result. After their surviving kids pleaded the judge for leniency before their sentencing, the couple avoided prison time. Daniel Rawlings pleaded guilty to manslaughter and his wife Lacey pleaded guilty to child abuse after what started as a joyride ended in the deaths of two 5-year-olds and a 6-year-old. Family members celebrated the decision, but the prosecutor says it’s not justice.

0tmkrUC10mY.title: Was ‘Playboy’ Hugh Hefner Secretly Bisexual?
0tmkrUC10mY.description: Hugh Hefner was in a romantic relationship with his personal physician, Dr. Mark Saginor, for nearly 40 years, according to Saginor's daughter, who told Inside Edition she and her father lived at the Playboy Mansion when she was a girl. "I am saying that Hefner and my father were soul mates," Jennifer Saginor told Inside Edition chief correspondent Jim Moret. "In my opinion, this was the love of Hefner's life and the love of my father's life." Saginor said they also had a physical relationship.

ggwh5UIcJjE.title: Meet Methuselah, the World’s Oldest Aquarium Fish
ggwh5UIcJjE.description: Methuselah just might be the oldest fish in a zoological setting on Earth. Known as the Australian or Queensland lungfish, it’s 4-feet long and one of only six living species of air-breathing lungfish. Methuselah came to San Francisco on a steamship from Australia back in 1938. Since then, it has been kept at Steinhart Aquarium, which is one of the most biologically diverse and interactive aquariums in the world. Inside Edition Digital’s Stephanie Officer explains.

ydLNBp-LfpM.title: Artist’s 3D Cat Portraits Look Like Real Animals
ydLNBp-LfpM.description: An artist goes to great lengths to create these life-like cat creations. She goes by Sachi and it can take her days to make one of her unique 3D cat portraits. Using felt, glass, and even real cat whiskers, she spares no detail to craft each individual cat. The most painstaking part of her process is crafting the cat’s eyes. She uses glass spheres layered on top of acrylic paint and sand in a process that can take up to a week. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

5Kjjiu4UPSI.title: ‘Friends’ Actor Tried to Bust Alleged Shoplifter
5Kjjiu4UPSI.description: Actor Michael Rappaport says he witnessed a brazen shoplifter fill garbage bags with loot from a New York City drug store and stroll out right past the security guard, who did nothing about it. Rappaport, best known for his recurring role as Phoebe’s detective boyfriend on "Friends," recorded the incident. He was so incensed that he followed the alleged shoplifter out of the store, giving a running commentary. He sent the video to the city’s new mayor, Eric Adams.

h6c1Y2qvRKQ.title: 19-Year-Old Becomes Youngest Woman to Fly Solo Around Globe
h6c1Y2qvRKQ.description: This woman touched down into the record books. Pilot Zara Rutherford, 19, just completed a solo trip around the world by plane, making her the youngest woman to do so. Zara took off from Belgium back in August and spent the next five months taking the globe by storm in her Shark ultralight microplane. She landed on five continents and as much as she enjoyed her journey, she says she’s glad to finally be home. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

gi5HlQY0AjU.title: Was Tiffany Haddish Asleep at the Wheel? 911 Call Released
gi5HlQY0AjU.description: Comedian Tiffany Haddish was arrested for driving under the influence after police say a witness called 911 saying he saw someone asleep behind the wheel of an SUV. It happened in Peachtree City, Georgia, near Atlanta. Police released the 911 call in which the caller confirmed that he saw a person asleep at a traffic light. Police made a traffic stop as haddish was pulling into the yard of a residence. She reportedly refused to take a breathalyzer test and was placed under arrest.

Gq3eYn8VeLI.title: Couple Who Got Trapped in Landslide Find Missing Dog in Rubble
Gq3eYn8VeLI.description: Six days after a devastating landslide destroyed a couple’s home in Washington, one of their dogs was miraculously discovered alive. The disaster happened after torrential rain lifted the home off its foundation and sent it sliding. James and Didi Fritts were trapped in the debris. Adding to their nightmare, they were unsure what happened to their two Labrador retrievers. Nearly a week after the collapse, the couple returned to what was left of their home in search of their dogs.

TYWhHe_2oao.title: 26-Year-Old Rapper Fatally Shot at Party
TYWhHe_2oao.description: Rapper Earl Swavey has died. While his representatives did not specify the cause of death, reports say he was shot at a party in his hometown of south Los Angeles. Swavey reportedly started rapping at a young age, releasing music in 2013 while he was still a teen. He released three albums in 2021. Fans and fellow artists like Vince Staples and Fenix are sending their condolences over social media. Swavey was 26.

wAHWl4KAD0A.title: Newborn Allegedly Tossed in Trash Found Alive in Dumpster
wAHWl4KAD0A.description: Three people searching a dumpster in New Mexico for valuables found a baby in a trash bag. “Their collective quick response to this emergency, including notification of 911 was absolutely pivotal in saving this baby's life,” said Hobbs Police Chief August Fons. Police say surveillance video shows 18-year-old Alexis Avila throwing out her newborn about six hours earlier. Investigators say she told them that she didn’t know she was pregnant until the day before and “panicked.”

BilOWKQ3Y0U.title: Why Hallway Fire Doors Should Always Be Kept Closed
BilOWKQ3Y0U.description: When Yesbely Fernandez saw black smoke pouring out of a lower apartment, she put a wet towel down in front of her closed door and stuck her head out the window until it was deemed safe to evacuate. Fire officials say the front door of the apartment where the fire started remained open, allowing toxic smoke to spread. Keeping doors closed during a fire can make a massive difference in terms of fire spread and smoke damage.

I7zs69SMoBU.title: Devotees of Hindu God Ayyappa Walk Over Hot Embers
I7zs69SMoBU.description: It’s a ritual for the truly devoted. Hindus in India gathered for a ceremony to appease the god Ayyappa by walking over hot embers. Lord Ayyappa is mostly worshipped in the southern part of the country. Son of Lord Shiva and the mythical Mohini, Ayyappa was said to be abandoned by his parents at the bank of a river. That’s where he was found by a childless king and adopted, having been considered a gift from the gods. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

zRzw9qKIQfM.description: The bluish cave has a rounded ceiling made of thick ice about 16 feet high. i6GMiWyxSzE.description: Neighbors reported “meowing” coming from an underground pipe in Phoenix, Arizona. He ran for days until the Arizona Humane Society and Phoenix Firefighters used a humane trap — and food — to lure him out. When he’s strong enough to leave the hospital, this furball is headed for the residence of one of the firefighters who rescued him.

s_SHTVDj768.title: Humpback Whales 'Sing' to Tourists
s_SHTVDj768.description: Tourists to the Mexican state of Oaxaca are being treated to a show only Mother Nature could choreograph! Humpback whales are making their yearly migration from the colder North American waters to the warmth of Central America. While people love to watch these 40-ton swimmers, government regulations say sightseeing boats should maintain a healthy distance from the whales. As for the humans, they’re still having a whale of a time watching!

5JTr5P0rhPA.title: Vacationer Fears She Won’t Be Able to Come Home
5JTr5P0rhPA.description: An American woman vacationing in Mexico says she can’t relax on her getaway because she fears that she will get stranded and be unable to return home to New York. Olivia Khoshatefeh, who is trying to enjoy the beautiful resort town of Tulum, is afraid that if she tests positive for COVID-19 before her return flight home she will have to find accommodations while she quarantines. She’s also worried that airport chaos could also prevent her from leaving.

LJD-uPTIgx8.title: New Invention Lets You ‘Taste the TV’

UNpsOdtyugA.title: COVID Fears Cause Cruise Ships to Be Turned Away From Ports
UNpsOdtyugA.description: One passenger on a cruise ship described her trip as feeling like a "superspreader event," saying that she felt she was exposed to a lot of people who weren't wearing masks. "It just felt like a petri dish," she says of the cruise, with ship staff spotted in Hazmat suits. She says the ship was even turned away at a Caribbean port. ZCmpJezzFqM.title: Good Samaritan Tackles Purse Snatcher
ZCmpJezzFqM.description: When someone snatched an elderly woman’s purse, a good Samaritan nearby didn’t hesitate to jump into action. The heroic act was captured on surveillance video outside a supermarket in Ohio. The victim was 87-year-old Pat Coins, who was shopping when the bad guy snatched her purse. That's when Deshawn Pressley jumped into action. After tackling the fleeing purse snatcher, he held him down until cops arrived. Now the Butler County sheriff is honoring Pressley for his heroism.

CdUFL0j4cDk.title: Walmart Limits How Many COVID-19 Test Kits You Can Buy
CdUFL0j4cDk.description: With just three days left before Christmas, the lines to get a COVID-19 test are getting longer and longer. Making a tough situation even worse, some testing sites have shut down because they don’t have enough medical personnel to deal with the crisis. Rapid test kits are all but impossible to find, even online. Walmart is lowering its cap on how many at-home tests customers can buy online, citing limited inventory and high demand.

This year he drew a fox in a frozen lake in Finland, but in previous years he’s drawn other animals like an owl and a bear. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

UZm73w7fUdU.description: The Omicron variant is ripping through New York City as COVID-19 cases are doubling almost every other day. Lines are hours-long for tests, and home test kits are in short supply. Broadway suffered a disruption that echoed the early days of the pandemic. At the show "Moulin Rouge," the audience was already seated when the performance was cancelled after some of the cast tested positive. Matt Berthot, a high school music teacher from Kansas, was in the audience with his students when it happened.

v8QMFb2r8NI.title: Low-Rated 100th Miss America Pageant Called ‘Cringey’
v8QMFb2r8NI.description: The new Miss America was crowned last night with Miss Alaska, 20-year-old Emma Broyles, winning the title. But after years of plummeting ratings, this year’s 100th anniversary show didn’t even air on broadcast TV. Instead, viewers streamed it on NBC’s Peacock, and the reviews were pretty bad. “Cringey,” and “a mess,” posted disappointed fans. Many credit the competition’s downfall to ditching the swimsuit competition in 2018, and turning it into a scholarship contest rather than a beauty pageant.

hkgt7UU-KIM.description: A rescue dog was stolen from an animal shelter’s biggest fundraising night of the year, according to a board member of the shelter. Ten rescue dogs were brought to the event that was raising money for the Pawfect Match Rescue and Rehabilitation in Holly Springs, North Carolina. Ms. Persy, a Pit Bull mix was one of them. The shelter says surveillance video shows a woman pick up Ms. Persy and walk out with the dog and into a car.  A $1,000 reward is being offered for Ms. Persey’s safe return.

8KwWnWrlsJo.title: Delicious Food Art Used to Cover Hate Graffiti
8KwWnWrlsJo.description: Pier Paolo Spinazze creates art under the name Cibo, an Italian word for food. He says he was “sick of seeing” swastikas and other symbols of hate, so he started using his own art to do something about it. Some of Cibo’s over 365,000 Instagram followers will alert him when racial slurs or neo-Nazi graffiti shows up in public places. Cibo says his food murals are meant to combat the rise in extremism, and to inspire others to use their talents to better their communities.

WoT2tmPkoPA.title: Mini Taj Mahal is a $266,000 Monument to Love
WoT2tmPkoPA.description: Anand Prakash Chouksey spent 200 Million Indian rupees, or about $266,000, on recreating the famous Taj Mahal in honor of his wife. Chouksey’s son Kabir says making the mini Taj Mahal took several tries. “We wanted to make an exact miniature version of the Taj Mahal, perfectly to scale, to the centimeter,” he said. The original Taj Mahal was also a monument to love. It was commissioned in 1631 as a mausoleum for emperor Shah Jahan’s favorite wife.

l5aGG387ojE.title: These Race Cars Produce Water, Not CO2
l5aGG387ojE.description: Many auto manufacturers have turned to electric vehicles to limit carbon emissions, but Toyota isn’t ready to give up their combustion engines. The Japanese automaker is experimenting with hydrogen powered vehicles. The chemical reaction between hydrogen fuel mixing with oxygen in the air only creates water as a byproduct. Toyota holds over 5,000 patents on hydrogen fuel cell technology and offers them to other auto manufacturers royalty-free, to encourage more use of this alternative fuel.

ZYYw_7Tbd88.description: A Los Angeles woman is recovering after being held hostage last month for several hours in a high-rise apartment, where the suspected gunman was seen in a window holding a gun to her head in a viral video captured from across the street. They closed in on him at a downtown apartment, where the drama unfolded on the fourth floor. They threw a flash-bang grenade into the room and stormed in to save her, bodycam video shows. In the hail of gunfire, cops hit their target and shot the gunman dead.

0PIw-Y3Y9HY.title: Why Real and Fake Christmas Trees Are Harder to Get This Year
0PIw-Y3Y9HY.description: Dreaming of a beautiful Christmas Tree this year? Better get one soon! Jack Sangillo owns the Anne Ellen Christmas Tree Farm in Manalapan, New Jersey, and he told Inside Edition that the cost of importing the trees he doesn’t grow at the farm has doubled since last year. Artificial trees are also in short supply, as they mostly come from China and are held up in the supply chain chaos. But if you buy your tree too early, it could dry out and die before Christmas arrives, which poses a fire hazard.

UuQtqIMpIMM.title: Fire Safety Tips for Cooking Safely This Thanksgiving
UuQtqIMpIMM.description: Unattended cooking is one of the leading causes of fire in a kitchen, and Thanksgiving is the peak day for cooking fires. Inside Edition teamed up with Kidde, one of the largest manufacturers of life safety equipment, for fire safety tips that can help keep your family safe. YKX7QNfrL_M.title: Cow Saved From Flood Waters by Being Pulled on Jet Ski
YKX7QNfrL_M.description: A stranded cow was brought to safety with the help of a jet ski. It was one of about 50 cattle that found themselves almost underwater after a farm flooded. A few people helped push the cattle to drier land. More cows eventually made their way to higher ground as well. Boats were also used in the rescue. Two days of torrential rain caused flooding in parts of British Columbia. Other areas have seen mudslides with at least one reported death.

UH8V7dSH2zs.title: Injured Deer Prances Into Hospital Seeking Medical Help
UH8V7dSH2zs.description: This deer somehow knew exactly where to seek help: the hospital. It appeared to be in distress as it wandered in through the main entrance and then climbed up the downward escalator, hospital employees say. Employee Judy Maddox watched as the deer slipped on the floor, prancing to find a doctor at the Our Lady of the Lake hospital in Baton Rouge, Louisiana. The deer was eventually sedated and rolled out. Sadly, due to its injuries the deer had to be euthanized.

GiWqn_RSmXs.title: The Rockefeller Center Christmas Tree is Up
GiWqn_RSmXs.description: A glistening signal that the holiday season is here stands tall in New York City’s Rockefeller Center. Each year a tree is plucked from a different state around the country and brought to the center of Manhattan. It will be adorned with 50,000 lights topped with a 900-pound star that has 70 spikes covered in 3 million crystals. “We just stood it up and it looks absolutely gorgeous," said Erik Pauze, Head Gardener at Rockefeller Center. Inside Edition Digital’s Stephanie Officer explains.

alpq_5dK1mo.title: Would You Scale One of New York City’s Tallest Buildings?
alpq_5dK1mo.description: After you climb 45 stories clad in a bright-blue, full bodysuit and are strapped into a harness, you have a choice to make: decide if you want to lean back hands-free 1,300 feet in the air off of 30 Hudson Yards, or simply marvel at the view while holding on. Daredevils and thrill-seekers would enjoy getting an unobstructed view of New York City’s iconic skyline, as they come face to face with it. Inside Edition Digital’s Stephanie Officer has the details.

eDb91vHVM1o.title: Many Think Kyle Rittenhouse Was Faking Tears on Witness Stand
eDb91vHVM1o.description: When Kyle Rittenhouse took the stand at his murder trial, he gasped for air and scrunched his face as he testified about the chaotic night that he opened fire in Kenosha, Wisconsin, last year, killing two and injuring another. But was he faking it? NBA star LeBron James was among many skeptics. “What tears???? I don’t see one. Man knock it off!” he tweeted. Forensic psychiatrist Dr. Keith Ablow says people watching the trial will believe whatever their sympathies predispose them to believe.

UNac_ppTpyQ.title: How to Make Your Own Bacon While Prices Are High
UNac_ppTpyQ.description: Bringing home the bacon just got a lot more expensive. Bacon is up 20% from last year, the highest price it’s been for 40 years. If the $15-per-pound price tag is a little too much for you to stomach, yet you can’t go without your bacon, you can actually make your own. Chef Franklin Becker of Oliva NYC showed Inside Edition’s Les Trent how to make bacon by using pork belly, which goes for about $5 per pound.

Y41lI46rsQc.title: Police Save Woman From Car Sinking Into Canal
Y41lI46rsQc.description: Officers in Florida realized time was not on their side as a car was sinking with the driver still inside. After heavy rains in Port Orange, a car ran off the road and into a canal. Ordinary citizens tried to help the woman trapped in the car until police could arrive. An officer’s bodycam caught the whole ordeal. They tried breaking the back window hoping she would be able to exit that way, but it wasn’t that simple. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

ntlSh0_0-b8.title: New York City Marathon Racers Help Fallen Runner Finish
ntlSh0_0-b8.description: It’s the video from the New York City Marathon that’s inspiring people around the world. An exhausted runner is helped to the finish line by two total strangers, who gave up focus on their own times to help him. Jamel Melville, the stricken runner, was running his first New York City Marathon, but his legs gave out with the finish line in sight. Andrew Sboner and Craig Astriecher saw Jamel go down, and helped get him on his feet. Each supported one of his arms as they finished together.

3OyjhSNita0.title: Pastor Tackles Alleged Gunman Who Stormed Church Altar
3OyjhSNita0.description: A pastor tackled an alleged gunman and his congregation held him until police arrived. A Sunday worship service was in full swing at Nashville Light Mission Pentecostal Church when authorities say Dezire Baganda walked onto the pulpit brandishing a gun. Pastor Ezekiel Ndikumana snuck behind the suspect and tackled him to the ground. Church members rushed in to help, taking away the gun and holding the suspect until authorities arrived.

_wIB5gnY8gc.title: ‘Stranger Things’ Stores Pop up in New York, Los Angeles
_wIB5gnY8gc.description:
Fans of the hit Netflix show set in the 1980s can rejoice. Netflix has opened ‘Stranger
Things’ pop-up stores on both coasts, in New York and Los Angeles on what is known as
‘Stranger Things Day.” The stores opened over the weekend on November 6th, a date
significant to the show (no spoilers!). The immersive experience also includes merch and
will only be open for a limited time. Inside Edition Digital’s Stephanie Officer has the details.

vtbGk16mA0g.title: Ash ‘Eats’ Resort Town
vtbGk16mA0g.description: Homes and luxury dwellings on the island of La Palma have been buried under feet of volcanic ash, courtesy of the volcano known as La Cumbre Vieja. Scenes of everyday life interrupted, including children’s swings and living rooms, look like something out of a post-apocalyptic sci fi movie. La Cumbre Vieja began erupting in September, and volcanologists don’t know when it will stop. Meanwhile, it continues to make the familiar strange.

yx6_h33Kk6w.title: Activists Wearing Fish Heads Make a Point About Oceans
yx6_h33Kk6w.description: Environmental activists with the group Ocean Rebellion donned fish heads while sporting fake fish and fake blood. Their theatrical protest took place in front of Glasgow’s River Clyde. Glasgow is hosting COP26, the United Nations’ climate change summit. The fishy activists want to make sure delegates at the conference don’t neglect the crucial links between the oceans and climate change. Olympic sailor Laura Baldwin spoke at the protest, telling reports, “We're sounding the alarm today."

a-Tc48yUxmY.title: Looted Artifacts Returned to India and Nigeria
a-Tc48yUxmY.description: Officials in both Africa and India have accepted the return of pricey and historical artifacts once looted from their lands. A Scottish University recently discovered they had a stolen Benin Bronze and contacted Nigerian officials to give it back. They hope this gesture inspires other institutions to do the same. Officials in New York City held a ceremony to return stolen items from India. Inside Edition Digital’s Stephanie Officer explains.

ob4gkOAdZRg.title: 2 Construction Workers Rescued After Falling in Trench
ob4gkOAdZRg.description: It was an all hands on deck situation to help two men get out of a trench on a construction site in Arizona. The Scottsdale Fire Department says a 43-year-old worker fell into the trench and got injured. They say another worker voluntarily jumped into the trench to help him. Fire crews from neighboring cities also showed up to help in the rescue operation which took four hours. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

WdK5apWQ_xc.title: TikTok Impersonator Accused of Murdering Estranged Wife
WdK5apWQ_xc.description: Ali Abulaban pleaded not guilty in the double murder of his estranged wife, Ana Abulaban, and another man, Rayburn Barron. Police say he shot both of them in a San Diego high-rise building on October 21. The suspect was known on TikTok by the user name “Jinnkid” and has nearly one million followers. People watched for his impressions, including one of Tony Montana from “Scarface.” Prosecutors Abulaban shot his estranged wife and Barron because Abulaban believed they were in a relationship. #InsideEdition

e1GLp-UNAyQ.description: Allen Brown made a purchase at a Kenosha, Wisconsin, gas station before going back to the SUV he allegedly stole. Outside waiting for him were dozens of Kenosha County sheriff’s deputies. Brown ran but didn’t get far, instead, starting a shootout with one of the officers. Police say he has a lengthy criminal record, including arrests for domestic battery and theft. Inside Edition Digital’s Stephanie Officer has the details. #InsideEdition

Iuig27UFCuc.title: These Barber Brothers Can Shave the Taj Mahal Into Your Head
Iuig27UFCuc.description: 29-year-old Rajwinder Singh Sidhu and his 31-year-old brother, Gurwinder, are the talk of Mandi Dabwali in northern India, thanks to their elaborate haircut designs. They can accurately recreate pretty much anything you can think of on a scalp. "Hair design competitions are held in the U.S. and Mexico and we will try and participate there and represent India to make our country proud," Rajwinder told Reuters. Inside Edition Digital’s Stephanie Officer explains.

dx8WAGlBn2A.title: 96-Year-Old Goes on Trial for War Crimes After Flee Attempt
dx8WAGlBn2A.description: A woman who went on the lam to avoid prosecution for alleged Nazi war crimes appeared in a German court. Irmgard Furchner, 96, was brought into the courtroom in a wheelchair with her face and head covered. She is charged with complicity of the killings and attempted killings of 11,000 people at a Nazi concentration camp between 1943 and 1945. Last month Furchner was a no-show on the day court proceedings against her were to begin. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

_doA11fWCMc.title: Which Royal Asked About the Color of Baby Archie’s Skin?
_doA11fWCMc.description: Andrew Morton, the best-selling author who has written about Princess Diana, is back with a new book called "Meghan and the Unmasking of the Monarchy,” and he spoke to Inside Edition about the similarities he sees between Prince Harry’s wife and his late mother. Morton also says that it is “beholden” to the couple to reveal who questioned how dark their baby’s skin would be, which was brought up during Meghan and Harry’s blockbuster interview with Oprah earlier this year.

O2ZgX94QoTA.title: 17 Missionaries Kidnapped in Haiti
O2ZgX94QoTA.description: Is Haiti’s most notorious gang, the 400 Mawozo, behind the brazen kidnapping of 17 missionaries in Haiti? The gang is believed to be one of the country's most dangerous and controls the suburbs of Port-au-Prince, where the missionaries were taken. That area has been subject to considerable recent violence, including gun battles between gangs and kidnappings of law enforcement officials. A plane filled with FBI agents landed in Haiti and are said to be negotiating the release of the missionaries.

sbrocEbnETA.title: Remains Found in Iowa Field Are Xavior Harrelson: Cops
sbrocEbnETA.description: Human remains found in Iowa on Sept. 30 were identified as those of missing child Xavior Harrelson. Authorities say a farmer reported having found possible human remains while doing field work and that clothing found near the remains matched the description of what Xavior was wearing when he was last seen. Xavior went missing on May 27, just days before his 11th birthday. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

In a GoFundMe set up for Pearson’s funeral costs, his friends write in part, “The only other thing that Chris loved more than his music was his family and friends. All Chris wanted was to make it far in life to help his family and make them proud. Chris was taken from us way way too soon.”

_GtX5E5WiLI.title: James Bond’s DB6 Is Getting an Upgrade
_GtX5E5WiLI.description: As Daniel Craig bids adieu to his time portraying James Bond, his car is about to get a second wind. David Lorenz, CEO and founder of electrification specialists Lunaz, told Reuters, "I want to preserve these vehicles for future generations to come. My daughter is three years old. When she's of driving age she'll be driving electric cars and I want her to enjoy vehicles like this." Inside Edition Digital’s Stephanie Officer explains. #InsideEdition #news

KdgBr3vxwRE.title: Student Arrested for Slapping Teacher
KdgBr3vxwRE.description: Educators are sounding the alarm about the so-called “slap a teacher” challenge on TikTok. But is it real or a hoax that has taken on a life of its own? Sickening video shows a student slapping and striking a 64-year-old teacher who uses a wheelchair. The incident was initially reported in connection with the “slap a teacher” challenge. But the school district in Louisiana tells Inside Edition, “We don't have any evidence from our investigation that this incident is related to the TikTok challenge.” #news

C9Ldd_VMxN4.title: Andy Murray’s Shoes Stolen With Wedding Ring Tied to Them
C9Ldd_VMxN4.description: Tennis star Andy Murray is making an urgent plea to find his stolen sneakers, which he says were damp and stinky the last time he saw them. But it’s not really about the shoes; Murray’s wedding ring was tied to them! The Grand Slam champion said he ties the ring to his shoelaces when he’s playing because it can’t keep it on his hand. He left his shoes underneath his parked car at a hotel in Indian Wells, California, to air out after practice. Now he’s hoping someone will reconnect him with the wedding band. #news

4NIIrmWcl40.title: Live Out Your 'Schitt's Creek' Dreams and Buy This Entire Town
4NIIrmWcl40.description: It may sound like the premise of "Schitt’s Creek," but there’s a real town in Tennessee that’s currently up for grabs. Water Valley was built around 1900, and sits on seven acres of land. There’s an original barn, four general stores, and a three-bedroom, three-bath residence waiting for someone to call it home. Realtor Crista Swartz says the owners have, “had a couple calls from Hollywood asking if they might buy the whole town to use as a movie set.” Inside Edition Digital’s TC Newman has more. #InsideEdition

lvzSaC7JPOc.title: Why This Mom Has Started Christmas Shopping Before Halloween
lvzSaC7JPOc.description: It’s not even Halloween, so why is this mom shopping for her kids’ Christmas gifts now? Mom of three Marisa Brahney has already started shopping for toys, because she knows that there’s likely to be long waits for deliveries as America’s supply chain faces extreme stress. More than 60 massive cargo ships are still waiting to be unloaded at ports on the West and East Coasts. Chris Brinkodski, owner of Tons of Toys, says that supply will start to dwindle at the end of October. #InsideEdition

Ti4NxKSCTRs.title: Protesters Follow Senator Into Bathroom
Ti4NxKSCTRs.description: Activist constituents of Arizona senator Kyrsten Sinema confronted her over her refusal to back the Biden administration’s Build Back Better plan, and went so far as to follow her into the bathroom. Sinema had been teaching at the Arizona State University campus, and avoided interacting with the activists, who pleaded with her. “We knocked on doors to get you elected,” one says to Sinema while she is in a bathroom stall. #InsideEdition

ddPk6gFrY60.title: Sorry, Newborns: The Future Looks Bleak
ddPk6gFrY60.description: A new study published in the journal “Science” says that people born in the year 2021 will face a future of unprecedented weather disasters, related to climate change. Those include droughts, wildfires, heatwaves and flooding. The study’s lead author, Wim Thierry of the University of Brussels, told CBS News, “Climate change is really a story of our own lives. The lives of our current children, current young generations. Acting now will reduce the burden on those generations.” #InsideEdition

2CozUVSYNz0.title: Prison Yoga Teacher Can’t See Her Students
2CozUVSYNz0.description: In the fall of 2019, Inside Edition Digital interviewed Chanda Williams, a teacher with the Prison Yoga Project at California’s San Quentin State Prison. But since the coronavirus pandemic began, Chanda has only been able to see her students briefly, and she told producer Mara Montalbano that she’s worried about them. “There's a possibility in all likelihood that some of the students who I've practiced yoga with over these six years may be infected and may actually die,” as a result of COVID-19. #InsideEdition

NAgM_h_a8KU.title: Remains Found in Iowa Field Could Be Xavior Harrelson: Cops
NAgM_h_a8KU.description: A recent discovery may finally answer what happened to Xavior Harrelson. Authorities in Iowa say a farmer reported having found possible human remains while doing field work. Xavior went missing on May 27th, 2021, just days before his 11th birthday. He was last seen riding his bike around the town of Montezuma, Iowa, where he lived with his mother. Since then, the +community has come together on multiple occasions to search for him. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

yxZHpT3aCJ8.title: Creepy Sculpture of Drowning Girl Appears in River
yxZHpT3aCJ8.description: People in the city of Bilbao recently woke up to a disturbing sight: a sculpture in the River Nervion, depicting a young girl, eyes wide open, who appears to be drowning. It’s the work of a Mexican artist named Ruben Orozco Loza. Titled “Bihar,” which means ‘tomorrow’ in Basque, the work of art is meant to provoke conversations about sustainability and climate change. The artist told a Spanish news outlet that he wants people to consider how "their actions can sink us or keep us afloat.”

v_JXlaSB6UA.title: Brian Laundrie Seen in Bar Before Gabby Disappeared: Patron
v_JXlaSB6UA.description: A new witness is coming forward to say he encountered Laundrie drinking alone at a restaurant in Montana on Aug. 26 — the night before Gabby Petito was last seen alive. United by grief, Petito’s mother, father and stepfather also spoke at the press conference — the first time publicly since the 22-year-old travel blogger was found dead in Wyoming’s Grand Teton National Park. The family also showed reporters new tattoos on their arms dedicated to and designed by Petito.

9ptK5NZ5BAU.title: 8-Year-Old Boy’s New Prosthetic Arm Made of Legos
9ptK5NZ5BAU.description: It was fitting day for Beknur Zahibekyly, but not for back-to-school clothes. The enthusiastic 8-year-old was getting a prosthetic arm made of Legos. His mother says finding suitable prosthetics has been a challenge. So, she reached out to a popular YouTuber who she thought could help. David Aguilar is known by his many fans as Hand Solo. He’s also an engineering student who created a prosthetic arm for himself out of the famous toy bricks. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more. #InsideEdition

cC1HUTgIFuM.title: It’s This Man’s Job to Dangle From Skyscrapers
cC1HUTgIFuM.description: Don’t look down! Jaw-dropping video shows a man dangling from the spire of New York City’s iconic Chrysler Building, 1,000 feet above sea level, secured by nothing more than a few ropes. Master rigger James Marksbury spoke to Inside Edition on more secure ground, just before he was preparing to go back out onto the spire. “It definitely takes a unique person to do this,” he says. “It's for people who are a little different, maybe wired a little bit different.”

W-freoo-__c.title: How This Supermodel Says Her Face Got Deformed
W-freoo-__c.description: In the 1990s, she was one of the most popular supermodels in the world. But for the last five years, Linda Evangelista has kept a low profile — and now we know why. Evangelista says she had a bad reaction to a cosmetic procedure known as CoolSculpting. The procedure uses freezing temperatures to help break down fat cells. Evangelista says she wasn’t warned about possible side effects, and she says her famous face has been disfigured as a result.

vJNXySfO-gs.title: ‘You Could Feel’ Brian Laundrie’s Temper: New Witnesses
vJNXySfO-gs.description: New witnesses have come forward describing a disturbing scene at a restaurant in Wyoming, in which they say Gabby Petito was “visibly upset” and cried as her fiancé, Brian Laundrie, fought with waitstaff. Nina Angelo and her boyfriend, Matt Englad, say that they could “feel” his temper as they watched the scene unfold. The incident reportedly took place on August 27, two weeks after their notorious run-in with the police after a fight, and just before authorities believe Gabby was killed.

bd12nkFnAWQ.title: Why Gabby Petito’s Cause of Death May Be Hard to Determine
bd12nkFnAWQ.description: Determining how Gabby Petito died will likely be a challenge given the amount of time that has passed. Though the FBI announced the discovery of human remains that resembled Petito’s description in Grand Teton National Park, the 22-year-old has not been seen since August 25. The remains were found in a remote camping area and were likely exposed to the elements, including intense heat and animals. The coroner will likely do a full workup, looking for traces of evidence as to how she died. #InsideEdition #GabbyPetito

6cktvbytFxE.title: Gator Trainer Says She Leapt Into Cage to Save Her Own Life
6cktvbytFxE.description: An animal handler who survived a gator attack last month is speaking out to Inside Edition about the harrowing ordeal. A gator bit down on 31-year-old Lindsay Bull’s hand during feeding time at a reptile and animal zoo, as children at a birthday party looked on. Bull jumped into the glass enclosure to get better leverage. Then the gator whipped the trainer underwater in what’s known as a “death roll.” She now reveals why she jumped in purposely, and how her gymnastics experience may have saved her.

O-FXrn7e1LE.title: Wildcat Gold Mining Is Devastating the Amazon
O-FXrn7e1LE.description: Illegal mining is booming in the Amazon, and that’s bad news for one the earth’s most important natural spaces. The Amazon is home to an incalculable array of plants and animals. A number of indigenous communities also make their home in the world’s largest rainforest, which spans several countries in South America. Every year, the Amazon absorbs billions of tons of carbon dioxide, making it a crucial hedge against human-caused climate change.

Vfks1L0CTc8.title: 6-Year-Old Says Jesus Talked to Her in Hospital
Vfks1L0CTc8.description: Little Zola has a rare genetic condition known as Ehlers-Danlos syndrome, or EDS. Her family wasn’t aware of her condition in 2018, when she nearly lost her life after a series of hospitalizations resulting from EDS. Eventually Zola began telling her parents about her near-death experience. Zola’s mother, Brittan, told Inside Edition Digital, “She just asked, "When can I see God again?’” Zola’s family started the non-profit Zola’s Zebras, to raise awareness of rare medical conditions.

diGfZe3LoL4.title: Widow Shares Photos of Husband’s Maimed Body Found at Resort
diGfZe3LoL4.description: The wife of a Texas fireman found dead on a wedding anniversary vacation in Mexico is speaking out for the first time on “Dr. Phil.” Earlier this summer, Jamie Snow and her husband, Elijah, were at a luxury resort in Cancun to celebrate their 10th anniversary. When Jamie went to bed, Elijah stayed up for a nightcap. The next morning, Elijah was found dead — his body was wedged inside a tiny window at the hotel next door. Jamie is now speaking exclusively with Dr. Phil about that fateful day.

When Jamie went to bed, Elijah stayed up for a nightcap. The next morning, Elijah was found dead — his body was wedged inside a tiny window at the hotel next door. Jamie is now speaking exclusively with Dr. Phil about that fateful day.

QWO_l9iYYIg.title: Elderly Couple in Burning Car Saved by Bystanders
QWO_l9iYYIg.description: Five brave bystanders banded together to save an elderly couple trapped in a burning car on a highway in California. A 92-year-old man behind the wheel was pulled from the inferno along with his 90-year-old wife. The couple has been identified as Ken and Joan Williamson. Marie McCory, who recorded the heroics on her phone as she passed by the fiery vehicle, spoke with Inside Edition. It turns out, there’s a remarkable backstory to the five heroes who rescued the couple.

t3xNydG1ov4.title: 2-Year-Old Running in Traffic Saved by Hero Delivery Driver
t3xNydG1ov4.description: Gerson Taveres had accepted one last food delivery when he saw a toddler out in the road wearing just a shirt and a diaper. The father of four parked his car and ran out into the street, waving his arms so other drivers would see them. Gerson believes the toddler was distracted by a game tablet he was carrying. Los Angeles Police have located the boy’s guardians and say the Department of Child and Family Services will investigate the incident.

VLVOAsEz8mM.title: Delivery Man Pushing Bike Through Flood Waters Sparks Outrage
VLVOAsEz8mM.description: As the remnants of Hurricane Ida battered the Northeast with historic rainfall Wednesday night, an unidentified man was seen struggling to push his bike through waist-deep water on a flooded Brooklyn street with a plastic bag of food in tow. The video sparked mixed reactions on social media. The photographer who captured the video hopes to track down the man and give him proceeds he made from selling the footage. “I just felt depressed at the whole scene,” the photographer told Inside Edition.

PqpUjMi6hDo.title: Bears Wander Freely Through Evacuated Town
PqpUjMi6hDo.description: After the vast majority of residents evacuated from South Lake Tahoe to escape the Caldor wildfires, bears are taking over the resort town. With all the humans gone, the animals suddenly have the town all to themselves. One bear hangs out in a trash bin before wandering off in search of other food. Inside Edition spoke with South Lake Tahoe resident Todd Johnon, who is hoping his home will survive the approaching flames. After fire insurance prices spiked, he was forced to cancel it.
