PS2WJAB3_68.title: Armed Taliban Surround Terrified News Anchor on Broadcast
PS2WJAB3_68.description: The United States has completed its withdrawal from Afghanistan, but danger and controversy remain. An Afghan news anchor looked terrified as he was surrounded by Taliban members with rifles on a broadcast appealing to Afghans not to leave the country. President Biden took heat from two gold star families grieving the loss of their children in the Kabul airport attack. Lance Corporal Jared Schmitz’s father, Mark, was infuriated when Biden appeared to check his watch as coffins were unloaded. #InsideEdition

NVGG41c4Rio.title: Man Attacked With Hatchet at ATM
NVGG41c4Rio.description: A man at a New York City cash machine was brutally attacked by a man who came in behind him and started swinging a hatchet at him. The stunned victim tried to shield himself with his backpack, but the blows rained down in a disturbing flurry. People withdrawing money are tempting targets: your back is turned, you’re probably alone, and you’re there to get cash. Inside Edition security consultant Steve Kardian shows how to deal with a hatchet attacker when you’re at an ATM. #InsideEdition

EWPMJcxchoQ.title: Chaos at Afghanistan Airport
EWPMJcxchoQ.description: The sounds of gunfire ring through the air as people run toward the airport in Kabul, Afghanistan, hoping for a way out of the unstable country. This comes as Taliban forces have reportedly taken over city-by-city, while American and NATO troops withdraw from Afghanistan after 20 years. Afghan President Ashraf Ghani has fled the country, saying in a Facebook post that he felt it was best to avoid bloodshed. He also promised to “always continue to serve” Afghanistan. #InsideEdition

uOClxnofE3A.title: Woman Arrested After Walking Dogs Without Leashes
uOClxnofE3A.description: A woman was placed in cuffs in New York’s Riverside Park for the crime of walking her dogs off-leash. She says at first the officers were going to let her go with a warning, but she did not have identification on her. Instead, she was taken to a holding cell and handcuffed for two hours before being released, she says. The Parks Department defended what happened, saying that what's not on video is the woman becoming confrontational and not cooperating when she was asked to show her ID. #InsideEdition

-18ZGnRU6nw.title: 23-Year-Old Arrested Suspected of 'Harboring' 14-Year-Old
-18ZGnRU6nw.description: A 23-year-old man has been arrested in connection with the Caitlin Winchester case. Caitlin, 14, went missing from North Atlanta High School on the first day of class. She was found a week later, over 800 miles away from her Georgia home in Arlington, Texas. Now authorities have arrested 23-year-old Andre Marcelis McNair, suspected of allegedly “harboring a runaway child,” which is a misdemeanor in Texas.

BWt4iPt_Vyg.title: Cops Wrongly Handcuff Realtor, Client and 15-Year-Old Boy
BWt4iPt_Vyg.description: A Black real estate agent, his client and his client’s 15-year-old son had guns pointed at them and were placed in handcuffs by police during a showing of a Michigan home Sunday afternoon after a neighbor called the cops to report a break-in. Humiliated, realtor Eric Brown and potential homebuyer Roy Thorne say this would have never happened if they were white. Thorne said he made sure to keep his son behind him as they were walking out, so that if he was shot, his son would hopefully be spared.

ngMn2sxA1fU.title: Woman Surprises Man With Kidney Donation
ngMn2sxA1fU.description: Carrie Kimball has just offered one of her kidneys to Robert Scarborough. Carrie bounces with excitement before sharing her big news, and once the sign that says “I’m Your Kidney Donor” is read, the screaming starts and the floodgates of tears are opened! This joyous moment is the culmination of a year of secret testing to see if Carrie was a match. Thirty-three percent of American adults are at risk for kidney disease, according to the National Kidney Foundation.

xyBRIGIieWI.title: TikTok’s ‘Timbo the Redneck’ Dead at 18 in Truck Accident
xyBRIGIieWI.description: A rising TikTok star has died. Timothy Hall, known as Timbo the Redneck to his hundreds of thousands of followers, was killed in a vehicle accident according to videos posted to his social media accounts. A friend posted to Timbo’s YouTube page explaining that the 18-year-old was doing doughnuts with his pickup truck when he was thrown from the vehicle and it flipped over and landed on top of him. Timbo’s mom confirmed his passing on TikTok. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

lokQ9cNqAV8.title: Man in Wheelchair Saved From Subway Tracks Just in Time
lokQ9cNqAV8.description: In a race against time, good Samaritans sprang into action as a man in a wheelchair fell onto the subway tracks at Manhattan’s busy Union Square station Wednesday. Dramatic video shows the rescue unfolding as an oncoming train was seconds away. The video, which was caught on camera by WCBS writer Lauren Mennen, shows one hero jumping onto the tracks to save the man and pull him out. Mennen said that the good Samaritan "didn’t think twice whether he was going to go on those tracks.”

UBQqwq6q8Gc.title: To-Go Booze at Airports Getting Federal Crackdown
UBQqwq6q8Gc.description: The federal government is cracking down on the airport to-go cup, blaming it for the crazy wave of out-of-control drunken behavior on planes. During the pandemic, struggling restaurants across the country got a lifeline and were permitted to serve alcoholic drinks to-go, and customers loved it. But airport bars often see passengers ordering jumbo-sized drinks, so they can get drunk before even boarding the plane. Steven Fabian wanted to see how much alcohol he could get to-go at the Newark airport.

fsFg6teoQyU.title: Bear Cub Recovering After All 4 Paws Burned in Wildfire
fsFg6teoQyU.description: A bear cub was saved from a wildfire, but now faces a long road to recovery. A couple in California went to check on their house, which was threatened by the Tamarack Fire, just south of Lake Tahoe. When they arrived they saw the bear cub walking around on its elbows and called for help. Rescuers were able to subdue him and bring him to Lake Tahoe Wildlife Care for treatment. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.

Q3hUzAye6ps.title: Dolly Parton Recreates Iconic Playboy Cover for Her Husband
Q3hUzAye6ps.description: Dolly Parton, the 75-year-old singing legend, recreated her iconic Playboy cover as a gift to her husband, Carl, on his birthday. “He still still thinks I'm a hot chick after 57 years and I'm not gonna try and talk him out of that,” she said. Dolly appeared on the cover of Playboy back in 1978, and vowed to do another cover when she turned 75. But now that she is 75, there’s no more Playboy Magazine. But she put on the vintage bunny outfit anyway, proving she’s still got it!

d4TVNaTer3E.title: Why This Guy Found 160 Bowling Balls Buried in His Yard
d4TVNaTer3E.description: David Olson was going to demolish the steps to his back door. But as he chipped away, he found a slew of bowling balls in various colors and weights buried under the house. The Michigan man found a total of 160 bowling balls while renovating his home, and was bewildered at how and why they ended up there. Now, he finally found the answer as to why they were there in the first place. Turns out, they came from a now-closed bowling-ball factory in the town, and were used in the house’s foundation.

ah90y6xDG-k.title: Texas House Explosion Leaves Block Looking Like a War Zone
ah90y6xDG-k.description: A Ring camera in Florida captured the moment a Texas house exploded. The violent explosion leveled the house in Plano, just outside of Dallas. The blast damaged other homes in the area, and six people were taken to hospitals for injuries. One person was reportedly in the home at the time of the explosion, and the others injured were in the house next door, according to reports. The Plano Fire Department believes that a gas leak in the home caused the blast, which is still being investigated.

Oz4K-s6DEsY.title: Woman Gives Birth in Gas Station Bathroom

Video shot by another woman in the restroom shows the new mom just after she gave birth, holding her new son wrapped in a towel sleeping calmly, unaware of his dramatic entrance to the world. #InsideEdition

6YZDNmO4H5g.description: Some kids in Maple Grove, Minnesota recently caught an enormous goldfish in the lake outside their home. ‘Monster’ goldfish are turning up in many freshwater lakes across the US. The big fish are former pets. When people dispose of them, they often end up in the wild, where they can wreak havoc on ecosystems. Experts say if you need to get rid of your goldfish, give it to a friend or return it to the pet store. #InsideEdition

kMgWRKFDq64.title: Doctors Remove Deadly Tumor From 5-Year-Old Girl
kMgWRKFDq64.description: You can say a series of little miracles led to 5-year-old Negalem to get a second lease on life. The child, who lives in Ethiopia, has been living with a massive tumor on her face since her birth. Her small village does not have medical care, but a U.S. government official who happened to meet her decided to do something about it. Thousands of miles away, a pair of doctors performed life-saving surgery on her. Inside Edition Digital’s Stephanie Officer explains. #InsideEdition

4omeBPz0MH4.title: What Is a ‘Micro-Wedding?’
4omeBPz0MH4.description: As COVID-19 restrictions loosen around the country, the wedding business is booming again. But many still aren't ready to celebrate with large groups of family and friends. That hesitation has given rise to scaled back, micro-weddings. A typical micro-wedding costs much less than a large traditional wedding. The smaller-scale celebration includes far fewer guests, lighter food and drink options, and a shorter run-time. #InsideEdition

HqVkekRT2fA.title: Why This Man’s Being Taunted by His Own Neighbors
HqVkekRT2fA.description: A New Jersey man did a “walk of shame” out of his home after he went on a racist rant against a neighbor and then challenged anyone who had a problem with it to “come see me.” Angry protestors gathered outside the house in Mount Laurel as the man was escorted away by police officers. He was sprayed with beer and taunted with obscenities as he left, many in the crowd his own neighbors. Some on social media are comparing the incident to the walk of shame scene on HBO’s "Game of Thrones." #InsideEdition

RLFJoFEe_1s.title: 13-Year-Old Girl Walks Again Because of Great Dane
RLFJoFEe_1s.description: Bella was born with morquio syndrome, a rare genetic condition where a person’s muscles progressively waste away, along with other painful health issues. Because of a 4-year-old Great Dane named George, Bella is riding a bike and swimming. Before George, Bella’s leg muscles were quickly deteriorating, but her family says after six months with him, her legs were strong enough to hold her own weight. Because of his work with Bella, George won the American Kennel Club’s Award for Canine Excellence. #InsideEdition

pLxd2NPcqGQ.title: Princess Diana to be Honored With Statue on 60th Birthday
pLxd2NPcqGQ.description: Princess Diana would have been 60 this year. The People’s Princess was renowned for her compassion, which she spread all around the world. As Britain prepares to honor her with a statue unveiling, Brits say they can only dream of the impact she would have had on the world had she not died more than 20 years ago. The statue of Diana was commissioned by her sons, Prince William and Prince Harry. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more. #InsideEdition

fSY2JXvjf4s.title: Pregnant Mom and Family Among the Missing in Condo Collapse
fSY2JXvjf4s.description: Those missing following the horrific collapse of a Miami condo are young and old, newlyweds, retirees, and even entire families. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more. #InsideEdition

JIyMgazxs7o.title: Polygamist With Family of 39 Wives and 94 Children Dies
JIyMgazxs7o.description: A man who led one of the world’s largest families died earlier this week. Ziona Chana lived in Northeast India with his 39 wives, 94 children, and 33 grandchildren. They all dwelled together in a massive, 100-room purple-pink building in a remote village. Reportedly, the family’s unusual structure made them something of a tourist attraction. The 70-something Ziona was head of a Christian group that allowed polygamy. The Chana Pawl sect was founded by Ziona’s grandfather in 1942. #InsideEdition

X-bufiQB_8Q.title: Statue of Liberty to Meet Her ‘Little Sister’
X-bufiQB_8Q.description: Another Statue of Liberty is headed to America! Standing just over 9 feet tall, Little Lady Liberty is 16 times smaller than the Statue of Liberty that has welcomed immigrants to the United States since she was gifted from France in 1885. While they may not be twins, the two statues truly are “sisters.” The smaller statue is one of 11 that were created using an original cast used to make the New York version of the Statue of Liberty. #InsideEdition

-Jsgjvz6Lvg.title: Cicada Swarm Grounds President Biden’s Press Plane
-Jsgjvz6Lvg.description: A swarm of cicadas nearly made it aboard a flight carrying dozens of journalists destined for Europe to accompany President Biden's first foreign trip. After a 17-year hiatus, a swarm of Brood X cicadas has been consuming the eastern part of the United States in recent weeks. Takeoff was delayed due to "mechanical issues" after a cicada infestation clogged the plane's engines. The cicadas certainly seem to have a penchant for landing on TV reporters, but no need to worry, they’re harmless! #InsideEdition

CkWXBEScUJs.description: After 16 years as an elementary school crossing guard in Florida, Robert Frew is retiring at age 92. While he may have wanted something to fill his time after he retired from working at the phone company, this time he’s ready to retire for real, but not without getting a warm sendoff from the school community. On his last day, people turned out with signs of well wishes for Mr. Bob, as he’s affectionately known. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more. #InsideEdition

CBOqttRTYCA.title: Icebreaker Rescues Puppy Stranded on Iceberg
CBOqttRTYCA.description: Russian sailors conducted an unusual animal rescue last week, when they retrieved a dog from an iceberg. The crew of an icebreaker near the Arctic noticed the fluffy white pup, stranded on some sea ice. They lowered a ladder and called to her. The canine came in from the cold, and warmed up aboard the ship. The crew then called around, and were able to locate her owner. The dog -- a 1-year-old named Aika -- had wandered off from a Russian town near the Arctic Circle the week before. #InsideEdition

CVqXMt0eIxs.title: ‘Radioactive’ Rhino Horns Are Latest Tool to Stop Poachers
CVqXMt0eIxs.description: Conservationists in South Africa are trying something new to deter rhino poaching. They’re drilling holes into rhinos’ horns and inserting non-radioactive isotopes which will alert radiation detectors if and when someone tries to smuggle them across a border point. Since poachers won’t know which rhinos are carrying the isotopes, researchers are hoping it could make poaching a riskier business. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more. #InsideEdition

X07ZAQoZPFY.title: Serena Williams Supports Naomi Osaka Leaving French Open
X07ZAQoZPFY.description: Serena Williams is showing support for her rival Naomi Osaka after the young star withdrew from the French Open, citing anxiety and depression. Naomi’s stunning withdrawal came after she refused to hold a press conference in Paris, which is a violation of tournament rules. She was fined $15,000 and threatened with being kicked out of the French Open. Instead, she bowed out. Now other tennis stars are saying that changes are needed to take players’ mental health into consideration. #InsideEdition

ehjqx68Yzq8.title: Darnella Frazier’s Video of George Floyd Sparked a Movement
ehjqx68Yzq8.description: It happened on May 25th, 2020, but the historic saga sparked by George Floyd’s murder began the next day, at exactly 1:46am — the moment that 17-year-old Darnella Frazier posted the video she shot with her cellphone on Facebook. By daybreak, the video was circulating all over social media, and that evening three major evening news programs aired it. People were moved to tears, and soon after, to protest. An estimated 26 million people participated, making them the largest in US history. #InsideEdition

ZGD0uNLrZmg.title: Sunken Netflix Horror Village Reappears From the Deep
ZGD0uNLrZmg.description: A lost village that was featured in a Netflix horror series recently reappeared. The town of Curon was once nestled in a valley in Northern Italy. It was flooded in 1950 as part of a hydroelectric project. It was the perfect spooky setting for 2020’s Netflix horror series, “Curon.” Not long ago, part of the lake was drained to repair parts of the reservoir. And that meant that people could again walk the streets of Old Curon. #InsideEdition

The roles should be completely reversed, my son should be burying me.” Daunte Wright, 20, was shot and killed by a police officer named Kimberly Potter during a traffic stop on April 11 in Brooklyn Center, Minnesota. That’s less than a half hour’s drive to where George Floyd was murdered last summer. #InsideEdition

r9YIzLRAOyo.title: Noose Left in Black Family’s Backyard
r9YIzLRAOyo.description: A Black family in southern California made a terrifying discovery in their backyard earlier this week: someone had tied a noose to a tree. The family lives in Reseda, and wishes to remain anonymous. One member told KCBS, “I was panicking, I thought they know where I live, they know that we're Black.” The family believed someone cut through the fence in their yard to access the tree. The LAPD was called to remove the noose, and they are investigating the incident as a hate crime. #InsideEdition

He then fell into an unconventional friendship with greats like Arnold Schwarzenegger, Dave Draper and Zabo Koszewski. MMP4qiCDE3o.title: Arrest Made in 1984 Cold Case of Missing 12-Year-Old Girl
MMP4qiCDE3o.description: It was a missing persons case that had gone cold for three-and-a-half decades. Jonelle Matthews vanished without a trace after performing in a school Christmas concert in 1984. The 12-year-old’s disappearance gained national attention, but the case went cold. Then, in 2019, Jonelle’s remains were discovered by construction workers 20 miles from where she lived. Last October, authorities arrested 69-year-old Steve Pankey. He has pleaded not guilty and previously denied having anything to do with it. #InsideEdition

The allegations against 74-year-old George Tyndall span from 1989 to 2016. Tyndall turned in his medical license and was arrested when the Los Angeles Times published a Pulitzer Prize-winning investigation on the allegations in 2018. Since then, hundreds of victims have come forward. #InsideEdition

Producer Jensen Karp, whose wife is “Boy Meets World” actress Danielle Fishel, was about to pour a bowl of Cinnamon Toast Crunch when he claims he found something strange in the box. Producer Jensen Karp, whose wife is “Boy Meets World” actress Danielle Fishel, was about to pour a bowl of Cinnamon Toast Crunch when he claims he found something strange in the box. He tweeted at the company, who replied saying that it wasn’t shrimp, but clusters of sugar. But Karp says he was not satisfied and now plans on having DNA tests done by a lab. #InsideEdition

oOc1Uh2LNd0.title: Biden Presser Is Longest President Has Waited to Brief Media
oOc1Uh2LNd0.description: President Biden gave his first press conference since the inauguration, 64 days into his presidency. The highly anticipated event was carried on all the networks and cable news channels, and the tone was strikingly different from his predecessor's, which tended to be adversarial. Biden, by comparison, was quite dull. On the Late Show, Stephen Colbert and his guest comedian Dana Carvey faced off, giving their best Joe Biden impressions. #InsideEdition

E6VarZVOogQ.title: Stadium Seats Collapse in India
E6VarZVOogQ.description: It was a frightening scene at a sports stadium in India as a spectator stand collapsed in seconds. Dozens of people fell as the stand seemed to vanish from sight. Police reported over more than a hundred people were injured when the temporary structure gave way. It happened in the city of Suryapet in the Indian state of Telangana. The crowd was gathered for the 47th Junior National Kabaddi Championship. Kabaddi is a team contact sport popular in south Asia. #InsideEdition

rlwRRpIS0do.description: Officer Eric Talley was the first to respond to King Soopers grocery store, the scene of the deadly shooting in Colorado. He was one of the 10 people who lost their lives. Boulder Police Chief, Maris Harold calls Officer Talley’s actions “heroic.” He had been with the Boulder PD since 2010. According to family members, Officer Talley leaves behind 7 children, the youngest of whom is only 7 years old. Eric Talley was 51 years old. #InsideEdition

6w8WJYopHEs.title: Tinnitus Drove Restaurant Chain Founder to Kill Himself
6w8WJYopHEs.description: Kent Taylor grew Texas Roadhouse into a huge chain with more than 600 locations worldwide, but the restaurant tycoon ended his life following an unbearable battle with post-COVD-19 symptoms, including severe tinnitus. It’s a debilitating hearing problem characterised by intense ringing in the ears. Singer Demi Lovato revealed that she is also dealing with tinnitus, following her 2018 drug overdose. Experts say the high-pitched ringing can be deafening and incredibly irritating. #InsideEdition

xB5jDur4Np8.title: Old Toilet Trash Has a lot to Teach Us
xB5jDur4Np8.description: Joseph Bagley’s job as the city archaeologist of Boston, Massachusetts takes him to some interesting places, including centuries-old outhouses. Those old privies can tell researchers a lot about the people who used them. “The trash that people throw out into them, represents an unedited history. It's the stuff that people nobody thought would come and dig up in 100, 200, 300 years,” Bagley told Inside Edition Digital. #InsideEdition

cc8yD9UEGu0.title: Ancestors Can Come Alive Through Photo Animation Technology
cc8yD9UEGu0.description: A new app from online genealogy platform MyHeritage is bringing photos of departed ancestors back to life. “Deep Nostalgia” allows people to submit old family photos and animates them with smiles, eye movements and head turns. “What it does, is it gives you this connection with your ancestor — with those people in the images you see in front of you — in a way that is magical,” MyHeritage PR and social media director Rafi Mendelsohn told Inside Edition. Some of our reporters gave it a try. #InsideEdition

11A5_GjIXFg.title: These Animal Rescues Help Endangered Species
11A5_GjIXFg.description: Animal rescues are putting their best efforts into keeping endangered species alive. The world’s first platypus rescue has just opened in Australia with space to care for 65 of these web-footed mammals. Veterinarians in Chicago are bottle-feeding a month-old North American Otter. An elephant sanctuary is feeding milk-dependent calves while they learn social and survival skills. IVF fertility treatments are being used to save the Northern White Rhino from extinction. Inside Edition Digital has more. #InsideEdition

iaSHsQRGJRU.title: TikTok Helps Return Lost Vacation Video 30 Years Later
iaSHsQRGJRU.description: It’s a 30-year-old mystery - a family’s lost vacation video that went viral on TikTok. David Gutenmacher regularly scavenges through thrift stores looking for a cool vintage find. At a shop in Valley Stream, New York, he came across a videotape that showed a family on vacation in Africa, with images of a college student enjoying his time. Gutenmacher was determined to find who the tape belonged to, and posted it on TikTok. Amazingly, someone tracked down the young man, who’s now in his 50s. #InsideEdition

grD07KXlZ6c.title: Mom Bathes Kids in Pot of Melted Snow
grD07KXlZ6c.description: Children in a pot of hot water may seem like it’s straight out of a nursery rhyme, but this is actually a move from an ingenious mom. Dr. Marie Harper and her family found themselves dealing with rolling power outages and no running water because of snow and ice storms in Shreveport, Louisiana. In order to bathe her five children, ages 6 and under, Harper melted snow in a pot used for crawfish boils, and dropped her kids in one at a time! Inside Edition Digital’s TC Newman has more on their story. #InsideEdition

uzPdj6rpHbU.description: A pleasure cruise turned into a nightmare for one Florida couple when high winds and rough waters disabled their sailboat. After being stranded at sea for nearly a month, Marty Widrick and Sven Karrlson are back on dry land and speaking with Inside Edition about the ordeal. It was supposed to be the trip of a lifetime — sailing to the Caribbean island of St. Barts, renowned for its sun-kissed beaches and vacationing celebrities. But a day after setting sail from Fort Lauderdale, disaster struck. #InsideEdition

uPqQCTchyQQ.title: How This Ferret From 1988 Was Cloned
uPqQCTchyQQ.description: Cutting-edge technology is meeting cuteness overload with the first ever U.S. endangered species to be cloned - a black-footed ferret named Elizabeth Ann. She was created from the frozen cells of a ferret named Willa, who died in 1988. Elizabeth Ann’s cells were carried by a surrogate ferret and her birth was the culmination of a seven-year effort between U.S. Fish and Wildlife, the San Diego Zoo and biotechnology nonprofit Revive & Restore. Inside Edition Digital has more. #InsideEdition

4SVAFKyW20Y.title: CDC Now Says Virus Spreads Mostly Through Air, Not Surfaces
4SVAFKyW20Y.description: The unknowns surrounding the virus set off a worldwide hysteria last year, with people wiping down every surface they came in contact with, particularly after the CDC warned that COVID-19 could live on surfaces for up to a month. Now, medical experts now tell us that the virus is spread from person to person by coughing, sneezing, talking or shouting, which spread droplets. Now the CDC has updated guidelines to say instances of the virus spreading on surfaces is less common. #InsideEdition

pa428P0erxU.title: Joe DiMeo Gets Full Face Transplant in Historic Surgery
pa428P0erxU.description: The 22-year-old who has received the first successful face and hand transplant in the world is now back in the gym and working on his golf swing. Joe DiMeo, who lives in New Jersey, underwent the procedure in August after burning 80% of his body in a horrific car crash in 2018. Although DiMeo isn’t out of the woods and will be on medication for the rest of his life to make sure his body doesn’t reject the transplants, experts at NYU Langone, where the surgery took place, said it was a success. #InsideEdition

R3gef1Wn9BE.title: Fitness Instructor Makes Video During Myanmar Military Coup
R3gef1Wn9BE.description: A woman recorded a workout video while a military coup is going on behind her. Khing Hnin Wai‘s camera caught a convoy driving through a barricade toward parliament in Myanmar, once known as Burma. The country’s military seized control of the government from civilian leaders after claiming its recent election was rigged. Meanwhile, this dedicated fitness instructor was just going about her day recording videos for her students to do at home. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more. #InsideEdition

Se7kSVoLmX8.title: 33-Year-Old Mother Diagnosed With Lung Cancer Never Smoked
Se7kSVoLmX8.description: Mandi Pike, a 33-year-old mother of three, was diagnosed with lung cancer, but she has never smoked. She went to the doctor after a persistent cough and was initially misdiagnosed. At first thinking it was pneumonia, a scan later revealed it was lung cancer. A recent study showed that 12% of people diagnosed with lung cancer never smoked. Actor Dustin Diamond, who played Screech on “Saved By the Bell,” died three weeks after being diagnosed with lung cancer, and was also a non-smoker. #InsideEdition

IyTk9ZmVge4.title: Stranded Hikers Lifted to Safety in Blackhawk Helicopter
IyTk9ZmVge4.description: An Arizona National Guard team rescued three stranded hikers from Haribo Canyon, north of Sedona. The trio of out-of-town outdoor enthusiasts had been hiking and rock-climbing. They’d only planned to be out for a few hours, but when harsh weather rolled in, they were trapped in the canyon. They ended up spending more than 48 hours in the cold, with few supplies. One of the hikers, Scott Brand, told KPHO, “I was concerned about frostbite -- losing a foot.” #InsideEdition

UGC0XdJ8NpA.title: Why It’s Tough to Comb This 4-Year-Old’s Hair
UGC0XdJ8NpA.description: Taylor and Shilah are two little girls who were born with a rare genetic condition known as Uncombable Hair Syndrome. It affects only about 100 kids around the world. Instead of growing downward, their hair grows out in multiple directions. According to their mothers, it takes a lot of work to comb through the girls’ hair, and sometimes people can make rude comments. Shilah has an Instagram page to inspire other children who were born with this syndrome. It is believed Albert Einstein had Uncombable Hair Syndrome too. #InsideEdition

W6KTBtRQkBk.title: Woman Delivers Baby Thanks to 27-Year-Old Frozen Embryo
W6KTBtRQkBk.description: Molly waited a long time to join the Gibson family - about 28 years! At just over 1 month old, she has already made history just by being born. The embryo that grew into Molly was frozen in October of 1992, but she wasn’t born until Oct. 26, 2020. According to researchers at the University of Tennessee Preston Medical Library, her birth sets a new record for the longest frozen embryo to come to birth. Inside Edition Digital’s TC Newman spoke to Molly’s parents and the doctor who assisted in this new medical record. #InsideEdition

qDyLXG9BlZQ.title: ‘Robot Millipede’ Could Soon Be Coming to a Body Near You
qDyLXG9BlZQ.description: A team in Switzerland has developed a robot that moves just like a millipede. The Swiss Federal Institute of Technology recently unveiled its so-called ‘soft robot,’ which was inspired by millipedes. PhD student Richard Gu said, “This soft robot can actually generate a wave between the legs and actually propel to move forward using the same mechanism as a millipede walking.” He added that the technology may one day be used to deliver medical treatment from within people’s bodies. #InsideEdition

His protocol includes multiple pairs of disposable gloves, which he discards as he makes his way through an airport, searching for an uncrowded boarding area, then wiping down a seat in the waiting room. #InsideEdition

FRTYrwFaUmo.title: 500,000 Sharks May Be Needed for COVID-19 Vaccine
FRTYrwFaUmo.description: The race to develop a COVID-19 vaccine may mean that sharks will be in high demand. Shark liver contains a rare oil called squalene, which makes the vaccine more potent, and more than 500,000 sharks may have to be hunted and captured to supply the world with a coronavirus vaccine. Shark advocates like Stefanie Brendl are concerned about the long term effects. “We have to remember that there will be many other vaccines and this will go on potentially for decades and it will add up,” Brendl said. #InsideEdition

X5unQiRNExE.title: How a Global Safety Net May Save the Planet

Dinerstein describes the safety net as a map. “A map that basically says, ‘Here are the places that we need to set aside for conservation.’” He told Inside Edition Digital. “We have the power to envision a world that is much better than what we have now.” #InsideEdition

the incident. #InsideEdition

ns6Xu5dbva4.title: Chadwick Boseman Dies at 43 From Colon Cancer
ns6Xu5dbva4.description: “Black Panther” star Chadwick Boseman has died at the age of 43. The actor’s death from colon cancer was announced Friday on his Instagram. The post said “Chadwick was diagnosed with stage III colon cancer in 2016, and battled with it these last 4 years as it progressed to stage IV.” Boseman had not publicly discussed his illness, and his death came as a shock to millions of fans. 5ZDOIOslp80.title: Bats Get Coronavirus Tests in Thailand

Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more. #InsideEdition

caoLZPIB31s.title: How to Prevent Acne Caused by Wearing Face Masks
caoLZPIB31s.description: Face masks are an important tool in fighting the coronavirus, but some say they come with an annoying side effect: acne. Jen Kotkin is a teacher in the Phoenix area and says wearing a mask for a short period of time has been causing some skin problems. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more. #InsideEdition

ipo55iK9Mas.title: Wife Gets Job at Nursing Home to See Husband Everyday
ipo55iK9Mas.description: Mary Daniel’s husband Steven has Alzheimer’s and lives in a nursing home in Jacksonville, Florida. The home has been close to visitors due to the pandemic, and Mary had only been able to see Steve twice, by coming to his window. To make it so she could see him more often, Mary took an unusual step: she applied for a job at the nursing home. For two hours a day, two days a week, Mary washes dishes at the residence, and when her shift is done, she slips in to see Steve. #InsideEdition

anUO4NK0rVY.title: 1000-Year-Old Mill Is Grinding More Than Ever During Pandemic
anUO4NK0rVY.description: A mill in the south of England has been grinding wheat into flour since the year 1016. In recent years, it’s operated mostly for the benefit of tourists. But when the Coronavirus hit the U.K., it affected the flow of some goods like flour. So the mill operators decided to increase production to its former levels. Miller Peter Loosmore told CBS News, "It suddenly threw the clock right back to medieval times almost working the mill just as it used to." #InsideEdition

Former police officer Joseph James DeAngelo, 74, wore a face shield to the proceedings, which took place in a ballroom to accommodate a large crowd while adhering to social distancing guidelines. DeAngelo took a plea to 13 murders and more than 62 rapes that took place in Northern California between 1973 and 1986. DeAngelo was arrested in 2018 with the help of groundbreaking DNA technology. #InsideEdition

When they do, some people are wondering what a staple of Hollywood - the love scene - will look like. Amanda Blumenthal, a Hollywood intimacy coordinator, says stars may be hesitant to get so close together once filming starts up again, making love scenes more of a challenge. #InsideEdition

oCSomDy4SEI.title: Mom Who Gave Birth in Coma Finally Meets Her Daughter
oCSomDy4SEI.description: Angela Primachenko was 33 weeks pregnant when she tested positive for the coronavirus. She was admitted to the intensive care unit in respiratory distress. She was put in a medically induced coma for eight days, and her baby’s life was in danger. When she awoke, she learned that to improve her and her baby’s chance of survival, doctors had induced delivery while she was in a coma. A week later and for the first time, she was finally able to hold her baby daughter, whom she named Ava. #InsideEdition

InsideEdition.com's Mara Montalbano has more. #InsideEdition

usndc-Uo48c.title: Why President Trump’s D.C. Hotel Is Under Scrutiny
usndc-Uo48c.description: As the Senate is sworn in ahead of President Trump's impeachment trial, the former businessman's luxurious Trump International in D.C. is under scrutiny. Lev Parnas, the associate of Rudy Giuliani serving as a witness in the case who claims the president was aware of the alleged campaign to pressure Ukraine to investigate Joe and Hunter Biden, said he held meetings at the hotel. He also said Giuliani held meetings there as well. “It was like a breeding ground at the Trump hotel,” Parnas said. #InsideEdition

hwasvWplLac.description: One mom was horrified after watching video of her 5-year-old daughter getting put into a chokehold on a school bus. The little girl in pigtails can be seen and heard desperately yelling for help saying, "bus driver! Bus driver!" But the bus driver allegedly didn't intervene and the child broke down in tears. The mom, who asked to not be identified, told WFAA-TV that her daughter's life was at risk after one kid pinned her against the glass window and placed her in the chokehold. #InsideEdition

Lpll31SyxZ8.title: Headless Torso in Cave Identified as Fugitive Bootlegger
Lpll31SyxZ8.description: More than 100 years after a bootlegger on the run from the law met his grisly end in an Idaho cave, experts identified his remains. Joseph Henry Loveless is the man whose torso was found by a family in 1979. He was last seen in 1916 after escaping from jail by sawing through the bars. Authorities believe Loveless, a bootlegger, had killed his wife, Agnes. Thanks to advances in genetic genealogy, he's finally been identified. But it is unclear how he died, and his head has never been found. #InsideEdition

hdi2oQtB0As.title: Man Says He Cooked a Pork Roast In His Car During Heatwave
hdi2oQtB0As.description: An Australian man claims he cooked an entire pork roast using just his car. According to a post on his Facebook page, Stu Pengelly decided to do the experiment on a scorching day in Perth. He says it was over 102 degrees Fahrenheit outside,and he left the food in his front seat for 10 hours. He later shared video cutting into the fully cooked roast and eating a slice. With the heatwave continuing across the county, he may cook other dishes in the foreseeable future. #InsideEdition

iVt4aMMxnQ4.title: What Is Hanukkah?
iVt4aMMxnQ4.description: Hanukkah is a Jewish holiday that lasts eight days and the ways it’s celebrated vary widely, Rabbi Menachem Creditor, Scholar-in-Residence at UJA-Federation of New York, told InsideEdition.com. “The way that we observe Hanukkah has a lot of diversity, depending on what kind of Jew you are or where in the world you find yourself, but one of the commonalities is that it's a tradition to light the candles and to place them facing the outside world,” he said. #InsideEdition

gjNqzN9YKR0.title: Definitely Don’t Do This at Your Office Christmas Party
gjNqzN9YKR0.description: Two years after the #MeToo movement swept America, office holiday parties are on the rise. This year 76% of companies have held or plan to have parties. That's up from 65% last year, but don't expect drunken shenanigans of years past, says Myka Meier, author of “Modern Etiquette Made Easy.” She spoke about what party goers should and should not wear. “You actually do want to dress differently than you do at the office,” Meier says, adding “you can add glitter but don't show too much skin.” #InsideEdition

3v6BWUJ8w_M.title: Climber Reaches World's 14 Highest Peaks in 189 Days
3v6BWUJ8w_M.description: Nothing can stop Nirmal "Nims" Purja from making it to the summit of the world's highest mountains: not a dizzying lack of oxygen, not blinding blizzards and not terrifying drops. Purja, a Nepalese mountain climber and former British soldier, set out to climb the world's 14 tallest mountains as part of Bremont Project Possible. It's a feat that took the last world-record holder more than seven years, but Purja did it in just 189 days. Along the way, Purja set another six world records. #InsideEdition

jPsmk_KrJ0Y.title: Flight Attendant Claims Pilots Kept Camera in Bathroom
jPsmk_KrJ0Y.description: One flight attendant is making a shocking claim about two airline pilots, saying they livestreamed video from a hidden camera in the plane's bathroom to an iPad in the cockpit. Renee Steinaker says it happened on a Southwest Airlines flight from Pittsburgh to Phoenix. She says when she went into the cockpit, she saw an iPad mounted to the windshield showing video of one of the pilots in the bathroom. According to a lawsuit she filed, the pilot allegedly said it was a top-security measure. #InsideEdition

E2mf5oRUUPY.title: How to Dress for Halloween as Pennywise or the Joker
E2mf5oRUUPY.description: This year's hottest Halloween costumes are ripped right from the headlines. yZJ8p9W15qo.title: Tips to Avoid a Pumpkin Carving Nightmare
yZJ8p9W15qo.description: Halloween fanatics are getting out their pumpkins and carving knifes for some frighteningly fun crafts. But one slip of the hand can turn into bloody horror. There are some dangers that come with handling sharp tools, especially with kids around. So Dr. Duretti Fufa, a hand surgeon at the Hospital for Special Surgery in New York, has some tips for staying safe. She said to stabilize your pumpkin before you start and always keep your work space dry so you can keep a firm grip on your tools. #InsideEdition

k1t-cNJ8YGQ.description: Was Natalia Grace really a child when she was adopted by an American couple, or was she a woman posing as a little girl? Michael and Kristine Barnett adopted Natalia in Florida in 2010. They say they were told she was from Ukraine and had a rare form of dwarfism. Michael Barnett said the couple believed the girl was 6. The couple, who are now divorced, claim they were scammed into adopting Natalia, who is really a 30-year-old woman, they say. #InsideEdition

TPGln9IjbAM.title: James Corden Slams Bill Maher for Fat-Shaming Remarks
TPGln9IjbAM.description: James Corden is taking on fellow comedian Bill Maher after the host of HBO’s “Real Time” encouraged fat-shaming on his show. “We're not all as lucky as Bill Maher. We don't all have a sense of superiority that burns 35,000 calories a day,” Corden said Thursday night on his show. The situation started after Maher went on a diatribe on “Real Time” encouraging fat-shaming. “Fat-shaming doesn't need to end, it needs to make a comeback,” he said. Corden took Maher’s words personally. #InsideEdition

IxF_7Fa34JA.title: Baby Born 117 Days After Mother Is Declared Brain-Dead
IxF_7Fa34JA.description: A healthy baby girl has been born 117 days after her mother was declared brain-dead. The little girl was born weighing 4 pounds, 11 ounces and measuring 16.5 inches on Aug. 15, according to University Hospital in Brno, Czech Republic. "This case is unique not only in the Czech Republic but also worldwide," the hospital said. The baby's mother, who has not been identified, was 15 weeks pregnant when she suffered a severe stroke and was rushed to the hospital unconscious. #InsideEdition

8GMGxGEa3Zo.title: More Than 20 Alleged Jeffrey Epstein Victims Stand Together
8GMGxGEa3Zo.description: There was anger and tears as more than 20 of Jeffrey Epstein's alleged victims came together in a New York City courtroom for the first time Tuesday. "Today is a day of power and strength," Teala Davies told reporters outside court. "I want to thank the judge for letting us speak. It is still going to be a rough road but I'm helped by the other survivors who are telling me their stores," Jennifer Araoz added. Attorney Gloria Allred arrived in court with four new accusers. #InsideEdition

VYVJOKtecus.title: Is Spending Too Much Time in Space Bad?
VYVJOKtecus.description: Do astronauts lose touch with reality after going into space? That's the question a new movie starring Natalie Portman is asking. "Lucy in the Sky" follows a female astronaut as she struggles to adjust back to life on Earth. The film is loosely based on the life of astronaut Lisa Nowak, who lashed out when her former lover began dating another woman. Nowak drove some 900 miles to confront his new girlfriend, wearing adult diapers on the ride to avoid taking bathroom breaks. #InsideEdition

Tov_9tGq5p0.title: Pilot Records Selfie Video After Plane Crashes in Pacific Ocean
Tov_9tGq5p0.description: Video shows a plane crashing into the Pacific Ocean Tuesday during an aerial photo shoot involving two aircraft. One of planes during the shoot malfunctioned and crashed near Half Moon Bay, about 9 miles from San Francisco. The single-engine Beechcraft Bonanza lost power. Miraculously, the pilot, David Lesh, and his passenger made it out alive. As the plane sunk farther into the sea, the survivors gathered anything that would float and shot video of their entire ordeal as they tread water. #InsideEdition

dKWzN_3YorI.title: Man Sets New World Record for Fastest Men's Cycling Speed
dKWzN_3YorI.description: One man just set a world record, but he's already planning to break it. Neil Campbell is now the Guinness World Record holder for the fastest men's cycling speed for getting over 174 mph in the U.K. He surpassed the previous record set in the U.S. in 2015 of 167 mph. Campbell achieved this milestone on a custom-built bike attached to the back of a Porsche Cayenne pace car. But that apparently wasn't fast enough for him. He's already started a campaign to surpass 200 mph next year. #InsideEdition

eMaJOtOu5M8.title: Cop Tases 65-Year-Old Woman in Traffic Stop Gone Wrong
eMaJOtOu5M8.description: What started as a routine traffic stop outside Oklahoma City escalated when the 65-year-old woman at the wheel refused to sign an $80 ticket for having a broken tail light. Debra Hamil tells the officer in an exchange captured on bodycam footage she didn’t want to sign. The cop asks her to step out of the car and tells her she is under arrest. Inside Edition spoke to security expert and former police officer Steve Kardian about the incident. #InsideEdition
